INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2012-03-18 05:36:20','2012-03-18 05:36:20','Vimbli exists to help you be more successful.\r\n\r\nOur goal is to increase your knowledge of yourself by being a partner on your life journey.  As you go through life there will be many transitions.  Our first solution addresses corporate transitions (think new job, new company, new boss).\r\n\r\nThe Vimbli solution uses your strengths, values and overall life goals as the starting point to navigate any transition.   Each transition is viewed as a learning opportunity, and is structured to allow you to achieve a successful outcome and to deepen your knowledge of yourself.\r\n\r\nWe have created an straightforward planning and execution framework:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Start with a view of what success looks like</li>\r\n	<li>Recruit a sponsor for your \"endeavour\", and share your view of success (Optional, but highly recommended)</li>\r\n	<li>Convert the \"success\" into the activities and relationships that will increase the probability of a successful outcome</li>\r\n	<li>Review progress and make adjustments throughout the transition (with your sponsor, as needed)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThese 4 elements are deceptively simple on paper, but extremely difficult in practice.  In order to make it as easy as possible we have developed a solution that automates most of the data capture and visualization.\r\n\r\nAt the core Vimbli integrates securely with your calendar, email and address book.  Currently we have Google (gmail and Google Apps) covered, we are working to add Microsoft Exchange.  In future we intend to add voice, IM and SMS as well.\r\n\r\nFor different roles Vimbli allows templates to give you a start to plan your our transition.  There is no short-cut on this piece you need to do the work to define what you want out the mission, what you will do to get it, and share the plan with your sponsor.\r\n\r\nCommunication with your sponsor is streamlined using personalized emails with your activity and goal information.  You own the update.  Before sharing it with your sponsor you have the opportunity to make edits to the content.  Yes you can add and delete.  What you share is your decision.\r\n\r\nWe have created Vimbli with you in mind.   The application will most likely live in the enterprise, but our intend is to serve individuals who want to live life to the full.\r\n\r\nThat is why we picked the name Vimbli.  A play on \"vim and vigor\", meaning \"a zest for life\".  We wanted to capture the energy involved in transitions and personal growth.  We are looking forward to have you on the journey with us.\r\n\r\nWhat would you like to see in a solution like Vimbli?  Let us know.','What is Vimbli about?','','publish','open','open','','whatvimbl','','','2013-03-29 18:08:47','2013-03-29 18:08:47','',0,'http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/?p=1',0,'post','',0),(4,2,'2013-04-01 07:23:56','2013-04-01 07:23:56','Vimbli exists to help you be more successful.\n\nOur goal is to increase your knowledge of yourself by being a partner on your life journey.  As you go through life there will be many transitions.  Our first solution addresses corporate transitions (think new job, new company, new boss).\n\nThe Vimbli solution uses your strengths, values and overall life goals as the starting point to navigate any transition.   Each transition is viewed as a learning opportunity, and is structured to allow you to achieve a successful outcome and to deepen your knowledge of yourself.\n\nWe have created an straightforward planning and execution framework:\n<ol>\n	<li>Start with a view of what success looks like</li>\n	<li>Recruit a sponsor for your \"endeavour\", and share your view of success (Optional, but highly recommended)</li>\n	<li>Convert the \"success\" into the activities and relationships that will increase the probability of a successful outcome</li>\n	<li>Review progress and make adjustments throughout the transition (with your sponsor, as needed)</li>\n</ol>\nThese 4 elements are deceptively simple on paper, but extremely difficult in practice.  In order to make it as easy as possible we have developed a solution that automates most of the data capture and visualization.\n\nAt the core Vimbli integrates securely with your calendar, email and address book.  Currently we have Google (gmail and Google Apps) covered, we are working to add Microsoft Exchange.  In future we intend to add voice, IM and SMS as well.\n\nFor different roles Vimbli allows templates to give you a start to plan your our transition.  There is no short-cut on this piece you need to do the work to define what you want out the mission, what you will do to get it, and share the plan with your sponsor.\n\nCommunication with your sponsor is streamlined using personalized emails with your activity and goal information.  You own the update.  Before sharing it with your sponsor you have the opportunity to make edits to the content.  Yes you can add and delete.  What you share is your decision.\n\nWe have created Vimbli with you in mind.   The application will most likely live in the enterprise, but our intend is to serve individuals who want to live life to the full.\n\nThat is why we picked the name Vimbli.  A play on \"vim and vigor\", meaning \"a zest for life\".  We wanted to capture the energy involved in transitions and personal growth.  We are looking forward to have you on the journey with us.\n\nWhat would you like to see in a solution like Vimbli?  Let us know.','What is Vimbli about?','','inherit','open','open','','1-autosave','','','2013-04-01 07:23:56','2013-04-01 07:23:56','',1,'http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/?p=4',0,'revision','',0),(5,1,'2012-12-04 09:48:26','2012-12-04 09:48:26','','images','','inherit','open','open','','images','','','2012-12-04 09:48:26','2012-12-04 09:48:26','',1,'http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/images.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(6,1,'2012-12-04 09:50:16','2012-12-04 09:50:16','','images','','inherit','open','open','','images-2','','','2012-12-04 09:50:16','2012-12-04 09:50:16','',1,'http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/images1.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(7,1,'2012-12-04 05:36:20','2012-12-04 05:36:20','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision','','','2012-12-04 05:36:20','2012-12-04 05:36:20','',1,'http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/?p=7',0,'revision','',0),(8,1,'2012-12-04 09:51:00','2012-12-04 09:51:00','<a href=\"http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/images.jpeg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-5\" title=\"images\" src=\"http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/images.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"158\" height=\"149\" /></a>Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision-2','','','2012-12-04 09:51:00','2012-12-04 09:51:00','',1,'http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/?p=8',0,'revision','',0),(176,1,'2013-03-29 00:07:20','2013-03-29 00:07:20','','iStock_000021386717Large-004','','inherit','open','open','','istock_000021386717large-004','','','2013-03-29 00:07:20','2013-03-29 00:07:20','',106,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/iStock_000021386717Large-004.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(177,1,'2013-03-29 00:34:21','2013-03-29 00:34:21','','logo-1024','','inherit','open','open','','logo-1024','','','2013-03-29 00:34:21','2013-03-29 00:34:21','',106,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/logo-1024.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(178,1,'2013-03-29 15:12:00','2013-03-29 15:12:00','','iStock_000021386717Large-004','','inherit','open','open','','istock_000021386717large-004-2','','','2013-03-29 15:12:00','2013-03-29 15:12:00','',106,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/iStock_000021386717Large-0041.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(179,1,'2013-03-29 15:15:47','2013-03-29 15:15:47','','vimbli square icon','','inherit','open','open','','vimbli-square-icon','','','2013-03-29 15:15:47','2013-03-29 15:15:47','',106,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/vimbli-square-icon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(180,1,'2013-02-18 23:51:33','2013-02-18 23:51:33','Vimbli exists to help you be more successful.\r\n\r\nOur goal is to increase your knowledge of yourself by being a partner on your life journey.  As you go through life there will be many transitions.  Our first solution addresses corporate transitions.\r\n\r\nThe Vimbli solution uses your strengths, values and overall life goals as the starting point to navigate any transition.   Each transition is viewed as a learning opportunity, and is structured to allow you to achieve a successful outcome and to deepen your knowledge of yourself.\r\n\r\nWe have created an straightforward planning and execution framework:\r\n\r\n1.  Start with a view of what success looks like and share with\r\n\r\n2.  Convert the \"success\" into the activities and relationships required\r\n\r\n3.  Review progress and make adjustments throughout the transition\r\n\r\nThese 3 elements are deceptively simple on paper, but extremely difficult to execute in practice.  In order to make it as easy as possible we have developed a solution that automates most of the data capture and visualization.\r\n\r\nAt the core Vimbli integrates securely with your calendar, email and address book.  Currently we have Google (gmail and Google Apps) covered, we are working to add Microsoft Exchange, Apple and Yahoo!.  In future we intend to add voice and text events as well.\r\n\r\nFor different roles Vimbli allows templates to give you a start to plan your our transition.  There is no short-cut on this piece you need to do the work to define what you want out the mission, what you will do to get it, and share the plan with your sponsor.\r\n\r\nCommunication with your sponsor is streamlined using personalized emails with your activity and goal information.  You own the update.  Before sharing it with your sponsor you have the opportunity to make edits to the content.  Yes you can add and delete.  What you share is your decision.\r\n\r\nWe have created Vimbli with you in mind.   The application will most likely live in the enterprise, but our intend is to serve individuals who want to live life to the full.\r\n\r\nThat is why we picked the name Vimbli.  A play on \"vim and vigor\".  We wanted to capture the energy involved in transitions and personal growth.  We are looking forward to have you on the journey with us.\r\n\r\nWhat would you like to see in a solution like Vimbli?  Let us know.','What is Vimbli all about?','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision-6','','','2013-02-18 23:51:33','2013-02-18 23:51:33','',1,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?p=180',0,'revision','',0),(10,1,'2012-12-04 10:40:42','2012-12-04 10:40:42','','images2','','inherit','open','open','','images2','','','2012-12-04 10:40:42','2012-12-04 10:40:42','',0,'http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/images2.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(236,1,'2013-04-14 20:38:42','2013-04-14 20:38:42','[caption id=\"attachment_230\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\" wp-image-230 \" title=\"Personal Goals - Survey\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Personal-Goals.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"263\" /> From the Vimbli Survey: Words used to describe personal plans[/caption]\r\n\r\nWe will start analysis of the data from the \"What Mattered Most\" <a title=\"New Job Success Survey\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/NewJobSuccess\" target=\"_blank\">survey</a> on April 14.  The close will be \"soft\".  The first version of the report will be based on responses collected through April 14, 2013.\r\n\r\nYou have the opportunity to influence the report structure.  Below is the working structure for the report:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Background and Objectives</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Profile of corporate support </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Overview of the individual approach and experience </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Personal Plan</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Influencer Insights</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Values</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Strengths</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Self assessment of performance and engagement</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Assessment of the most valuable elements</span></li>\r\n	<li>Potential actions for the employer and the employee</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Demographics and survey approach</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 15.555556297302246px; line-height: 26.666667938232422px;\">What do you like? What is missing? Let us know what you want by using the comments below or email the questions via the contact options.  </span></div>\r\nIf you want a copy of the survey results make sure you <a title=\"Complete the New Job Success Now!\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/NewJobSuccess\" target=\"_blank\">complete the survey</a>, and provide your email.','Want to shape the survey report? This is your chance!','','inherit','open','open','','229-revision-5','','','2013-04-14 20:38:42','2013-04-14 20:38:42','',229,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/229-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(234,1,'2013-04-14 19:02:41','2013-04-14 19:02:41','[caption id=\"attachment_230\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-230\" title=\"Personal Goals - Survey\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Personal-Goals.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"263\" /> Visual display of common words used to describe personal plans.[/caption]\r\n\r\nWe are closing the \"What Mattered Most\" <a title=\"New Job Success Survey\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/NewJobSuccess\" target=\"_blank\">survey</a> on April 14.  The close will be \"soft\".  We will complete the analysis based on the responses collected through April 14, and will update the report on a regular basis going forward.\r\n\r\nYou have the opportunity to influence the report structure.  Below is the working structure for the report:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Background and Objectives</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Profile of support received during the role change</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Overview of the individual approach and experience </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Personal Plan</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Insight on influencer</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Values</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Strengths</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Self assessment of performance and engagement</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Assessment of the most valuable elements in an onboarding program</span></li>\r\n	<li>Potential actions to consider as employer and employee</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Demographics and survey approach</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 15.555556297302246px; line-height: 26.666667938232422px;\">What do you like? What is missing? Let us know what you want by using the comments below or email the questions via the contact options.  </span></div>\r\nIf you want a copy of the survey results make sure you <a title=\"Complete the New Job Success Now!\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/NewJobSuccess\" target=\"_blank\">complete the survey</a>, and provide your email.','Want to shape the survey report? This is your chance!','','inherit','open','open','','229-revision-3','','','2013-04-14 19:02:41','2013-04-14 19:02:41','',229,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/229-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(91,1,'2013-04-04 18:56:44','2013-04-04 18:56:44','Know where you are coming from\n\nKnow where you want to go\n\nKnow what this current \"moment\" contributes to the journey\n\nKnow your sponsors and share your goals with them\n\nKnow your support and share your goals with them\n\nBe deliberate your your actions\n\nEnjoy the moment','7 Keys to Success in Your New Role (... really for most \"NEW\" situations)','','inherit','open','open','','89-autosave','','','2013-04-04 18:56:44','2013-04-04 18:56:44','',89,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/?p=91',0,'revision','',0),(208,1,'2013-04-08 01:12:30','2013-04-08 01:12:30','<a href=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-210\" title=\"First Minutes Count\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"193\" /></a>\r\n\r\nOne of the core Vimbli value propositions is \"new hire ownership\" of their transition.  We believe the individual is best positioned to execute their transition into a new role.  The company can and should support the change, but the individual needs to step up and really own the transition.\r\n\r\nRecent research published in Working Knowledge, an online Harvard Business School publication, supports  the focus on the individual as an important driver of a successful onboarding.\r\n\r\nIn <em><a title=\"The First Minutes Count - HBS Working Knowledge\" href=\"http://hbswk.hbs.edu/item/7193.html?wknews=04032013\" target=\"_blank\">First Minutes are Critical in New-Employee Orientation</a>,</em> Carmen Noble shares new research by Daniel M. Cable, Francesca Gino and Bradley R. Staats.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\nHere is the quick summary:  Many believe the first few months are key to new hire performance and engagement.  Few get it right. The research indicates companies focus too much on the company and not enough on the new hire.  Most of the messages in the first days and weeks are primarily about the company.  Read the <a title=\"The First Minutes Count - HBS Working Knowledge\" href=\"http://hbswk.hbs.edu/item/7193.html?wknews=04032013\" target=\"_blank\">full article</a> in Working Knowledge for  details on how Wipro determined focusing on the individual resulted in more than 25 percent better retention than the traditional company-focused program.\r\n\r\n<em>The researchers are currently expanding the study.  If your company is interested in participating, please contact Francesca Gino directly at <a href=\"mailto:fgino@hbs.edu\">fgino@hbs.edu</a>.</em>\r\n\r\n***\r\n\r\n<em>If you liked the \"Minutes\" article and want to learn more about the latest research by Francesca check out her latest book <a title=\"Get Your Decisions to Stick - Get Sidetracked!\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Sidetracked-Decisions-Derailed-Stick-Plan/dp/1422142698\">Sidetracked</a>.  Sidetracked provides a framework to help you understand these influences, and provide tips and tricks on how you can get more of your decisions to stick!</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','The First Minutes Count (Harvard Research)','','publish','open','open','','the-first-minutes-count-harvard-research','','','2013-04-08 02:26:25','2013-04-08 02:26:25','',0,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?p=208',0,'post','',0),(39,1,'2012-12-06 11:57:21','2012-12-06 11:57:21','','iStock_000005449225Large1','','inherit','open','open','','istock_000005449225large1-2','','','2012-12-06 11:57:21','2012-12-06 11:57:21','',0,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/iStock_000005449225Large12.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(38,1,'2012-12-06 11:56:57','2012-12-06 11:56:57','','iStock_000005449225Large1','','inherit','open','open','','istock_000005449225large1','','','2012-12-06 11:56:57','2012-12-06 11:56:57','',0,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/iStock_000005449225Large11.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(21,1,'2012-12-05 17:43:37','2012-12-05 17:43:37','Getting the job is awesome!  Celebrate, but get ready for the real work.\r\niStock_000005449225','iStock_000005449225','','inherit','open','open','','istock_000005449225large','','','2012-12-05 17:43:37','2012-12-05 17:43:37','',0,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/iStock_000005449225Large.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(233,1,'2013-04-26 04:22:43','2013-04-26 04:22:43','[caption id=\"attachment_230\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\" wp-image-230 \" title=\"Personal Goals - Survey\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Personal-Goals.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"263\" /> From the Vimbli Survey: Words used to describe personal plans[/caption]\n<p style=\"padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px;\">We will begin analyzing responses from the “What Mattered Most” onboarding <a title=\"New Job Success Survey\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/NewJobSuccess\" target=\"_blank\">survey</a> on April 15.</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom: 1px;\">You have the opportunity to influence the report structure. Below is the working structure for the report:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Survey background and objectives</li>\n	<li> Overview of how individuals approached and experienced role transitions:\n<ol>\n	<li>Personal Plan</li>\n	<li>Influencer Insights</li>\n	<li>Values</li>\n	<li>Strengths</li>\n	<li>Performance and engagement</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n	<li>Assessment of the most valuable elements of supporting a successful transition</li>\n	<li>Potential actions for employer and employee</li>\n	<li>Demographics and survey approach</li>\n</ol>\nWhat do you like? What is missing? Let us know what information y