tp://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?attachment_id=292\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-292\">esults May 2013</a>\r\n\r\nYour feedback is most welcome.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Vimbli Onboarding Report','','inherit','open','open','','291-revision-2','','','2013-05-28 19:14:16','2013-05-28 19:14:16','',291,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/291-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(297,1,'2013-05-28 19:22:30','2013-05-28 19:22:30','This report summarizes the early results from the Vimbli Onboarding survey.  You can contribute to the research by sharing your latest professional transition in the survey.\r\n\r\nWe hope the report will help you as you navigate life\'s transitions.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Vimbli-Changing-Onboarding-Odds-Survey-Results-May-2013.pdf\">Changing Onboarding Odds May 2013</a>\r\n\r\nYour feedback is most welcome.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Vimbli Onboarding Report','','inherit','open','open','','291-revision-4','','','2013-05-28 19:22:30','2013-05-28 19:22:30','',291,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/291-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(295,1,'2013-07-17 19:35:34','2013-07-17 19:35:34','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Vimbli-Changing-Onboarding-Odds-Survey-Results-May-2013.pdf\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-320\" title=\"Vimbli Report May 2013\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Vimbli-report-cover-224x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"224\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This report summarizes the early results from the Vimbli Onboarding survey.  You can take part in the research by sharing your latest professional transition in the survey.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We hope the report will help you as you navigate life\'s transitions.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Download your copy now:  <a href=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Vimbli-Changing-Onboarding-Odds-Survey-Results-May-2013.pdf\">Changing Onboarding Odds May 2013</a></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Your feedback is most welcome.</span>\n\n&nbsp;','Vimbli Onboarding Report','','inherit','open','open','','291-autosave','','','2013-07-17 19:35:34','2013-07-17 19:35:34','',291,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/291-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(222,1,'2013-04-08 02:26:06','2013-04-08 02:26:06','<a href=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-210\" title=\"First Minutes Count\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"193\" /></a>\r\n\r\nOne of the core Vimbli value propositions is \"new hire ownership\" of their transition.  We believe the individual is best positioned to execute their transition into a new role.  The company can and should support the change, but the individual needs to step up and really own the transition.\r\n\r\nRecent research published in Working Knowledge, an online Harvard Business School publication, supports  the focus on the individual as an important driver of a successful onboarding.\r\n\r\nIn <em><a title=\"The First Minutes Count - HBS Working Knowledge\" href=\"http://hbswk.hbs.edu/item/7193.html?wknews=04032013\" target=\"_blank\">First Minutes are Critical in New-Employee Orientation</a>,</em> Carmen Noble shares new research by Daniel M. Cable, Francesca Gino and Bradley R. Staats.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\nHere is the quick summary:  Many believe the first few months are key to new hire performance and engagement.  Few get it right. The research indicates companies focus too much on the company and not enough on the new hire.  Most of the messages in the first days and weeks are primarily about the company.  Read the <a title=\"The First Minutes Count - HBS Working Knowledge\" href=\"http://hbswk.hbs.edu/item/7193.html?wknews=04032013\" target=\"_blank\">full article</a> in Working Knowledge for  details on how Wipro determined focusing on the individual resulted in more than 25 percent better retention than the traditional company-focused program.\r\n\r\n<em>The researchers are currently expanding the study.  If your company is interested in participating, please contact Francesca Gino directly at <a href=\"mailto:fgino@hbs.edu\">fgino@hbs.edu</a>.</em>\r\n\r\n***\r\n\r\n<em>If you liked the \"Minutes\" article and want to learn more about the latest research by Francesca check out her latest book <a title=\"Get Your Decisions to Stick - Get Sidetracked!\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Sidetracked-Decisions-Derailed-Stick-Plan/dp/1422142698\">Sidetracked</a>.  Sidetracked provides a framework to help you understand these influences, and provide tips and tricks on how you can get more of your decisions to stick!</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','The First Minutes Count (Harvard Research)','','inherit','open','open','','208-revision-12','','','2013-04-08 02:26:06','2013-04-08 02:26:06','',208,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/208-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(221,1,'2013-04-08 01:50:02','2013-04-08 01:50:02','<a href=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-210\" title=\"First Minutes Count\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"193\" /></a>\r\n\r\nOne of the core Vimbli value propositions is \"new hire ownership\" of their transition.  We believe the individual is best positioned to execute their transition into a new role.  The company can and should support the change, but the individual needs to step up and really own the transition.\r\n\r\nRecent research published in Working Knowledge, an online Harvard Business School publication, supports  the focus on the in