approached and experienced role transitions:\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Personal Plan</li>\r\n	<li>Influencer Insights</li>\r\n	<li>Values</li>\r\n	<li>Strengths</li>\r\n	<li>Performance and engagement</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Assessment of the most valuable elements of supporting a successful transition </span></li>\r\n	<li>Potential actions for employer and employee</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Demographics and survey approach</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 15.555556297302246px; line-height: 26.666667938232422px;\">What do you like? What is missing? Let us know what information you\'re interested in knowing as it relates to managing career transitions and onboarding by commenting below or emailing your questions via the contact options.  </span></div>\r\nIf you would like to receive a summary of the survey results, please <a title=\"Complete the New Job Success Now!\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/NewJobSuccess\" target=\"_blank\">complete the survey</a> and provide your email address.','Want to shape the survey report? This is your chance!','','inherit','open','open','','229-revision-8','','','2013-04-15 01:38:56','2013-04-15 01:38:56','',229,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/229-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(217,1,'2013-04-08 01:13:33','2013-04-08 01:13:33','<a href=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-210\" title=\"First Minutes Count\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"193\" /></a>\r\n\r\nOne of the core Vimbli value propositions is \"new hire ownership\" of their transition.  We believe the individual is best positioned to execute their transition into a new role.  The company can and should support the change, but the individual needs to step up and really own the transition.\r\n\r\nRecent research published in Working Knowledge, an online Harvard Business School publication, supports  the focus on the individual as an important driver of a successful onboarding.\r\n\r\nIn <em><a title=\"The First Minutes Count - HBS Working Knowledge\" href=\"http://hbswk.hbs.edu/item/7193.html?wknews=04032013\" target=\"_blank\">First Minutes are Critical in New-Employee Orientation</a>,</em> Carmen Noble shares new research by Daniel M. Cable, Francesca Gino and Bradley R. Staats.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\nHere is the quick summary:  Many believe the first few months are key to new hire performance and engagement.  Few get it right. The research indicates companies focus too much on the company and not enough on the new hire.  Most of the messages in the first days and weeks are primarily about the company.  Read the <a title=\"The First Minutes Count - HBS Working Knowledge\" href=\"http://hbswk.hbs.edu/item/7193.html?wknews=04032013\" target=\"_blank\">full article</a> in Working Knowledge for  details on how Wipro determined how focusing on the individual resulted in more than 25 percent better retention than the traditional company-focused program.\r\n\r\n<em>The researchers are currently expanding the study.  If your company is interested in participating, please contact Francesca Gino directly at <a href=\"mailto:fgino@hbs.edu\">fgino@hbs.edu</a>.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','The First Minutes Count (Harvard Research)','','inherit','open','open','','208-revision-8','','','2013-04-08 01:13:33','2013-04-08 01:13:33','',208,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/208-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(216,1,'2013-04-08 01:12:30','2013-04-08 01:12:30','<a href=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-210\" title=\"First Minutes Count\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"193\" /></a>\r\n\r\nOne of t