uires a lot of effort and focus, but there are 5 common elements:</span>\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Your VISION</strong> of what success looks like:  Are you building cathedral, building a shack or pitching a tent.  Your answer will impact everything you do.  If you don’t have an answer you’ll probably need to buckle up for a bumpy ride ‘til you find the vision, and find the sponsor who shares the vision with you.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Your PLAN</strong>, with building blocks:  Something worthwhile needs you to do a few things, and to do the things well.  What the things are often differ, but in most cases a transition requires building and maintaining relationships.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Your Execution: </strong> Plans are great, but in the case of your own life you have to go and execute your plan.  Many other things in life you can get others to do for you.  Your life you have to live yourself.  Having others with you makes the journey more fun, but you need to do the living.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Your R<span style=\"color: #000000;\">eflection</span>: </strong> Few plans actually work out as planned.  Hence the name, \"Plan\".  Reflecting on your progress (and where possible working with your sponsor and possibly some advisors and supporters) is critical.  Regular reflection allow you to identify what work and what does not.  In many ways that is what a journal done well achieves.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Your Adjustments: </strong>Many people reflect, and reflect but never take action on the reflection.  Reflection impacts your plan in 2 ways.  You can decide something is working, and do more of it OR you can decide something is not working and make a change.  The latter catergory also includes achieved goals.  Celebrate your achievements. Celebrate your failures. Learn from it, make adjustments and move forward.  Sometimes the learning process takes a bit longer, and it is ok to give yourself time to complete the process.<strong>   </strong></span></li>\n</ol>\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Without the explicit commitment to do the reviews and adjustments you should not waste time on #1, #2 and #3.  Go and buy a lottery ticket instead.  Ok, maybe this is a bit harsh.  The truth is without Reflection on and Adjustments to your plan your life journey will be less complete.   Note that true reflection may lead you to opt to do less not more.  Each of us is unique.  You need to learn more about yourself, and live your life.  Just like I need to learn more about myself and live my life.  </span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You read this and it sounds black and white you need to figure out where you want to add your own color.  The elements identified give only the starting point for you to create your own transition. You have to make adjustments to fit your worldview, personality and capabilities, and also align with the company culture and the immediate business needs.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If you we’ll cover the elements in detail and also discuss how to personalize the approach to fit you and your situation.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In the meantime – What is your secret to a successful transition? If you have different tips for different transitions feel free to share.</span>','How to make change count!','','inherit','open','open','','80-autosave','','','2013-06-19 12:33:12','2013-06-19 12:33:12','',80,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/?p=85',0,'revision','',0),(86,1,'2012-12-11 09:44:59','2012-12-11 09:44:59','Just to see if it works.\r\n\r\nThis is a link <a title=\"Try me now!\" href=\"http://vimbli.com\" target=\"_blank\">THIS</a> to vimbil.com, let\'s see if it works.\r\n\r\nand here goes <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">a list with numbering</span></strong>\r\n<ol>