P','','inherit','open','open','','89-revision-2','','','2012-12-21 20:02:33','2012-12-21 20:02:33','',89,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/89-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(106,1,'2013-01-08 16:15:50','2013-01-08 16:15:50','[wysija_page]','Subscription confirmation','','publish','open','open','','subscriptions','','','2013-01-08 16:15:50','2013-01-08 16:15:50','',0,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/?wysijap=subscriptions',0,'wysijap','',0),(93,1,'2012-12-21 20:13:51','2012-12-21 20:13:51','Plan\r\n\r\nDo\r\n\r\nCheck\r\n\r\nAdjust','Take Action to Realize your Talents','','draft','open','open','vimbli','take-action-to-realize-your-talents','','','2013-05-30 13:30:01','2013-05-30 13:30:01','',0,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/?page_id=93',0,'page','',0),(94,1,'2012-12-21 20:13:23','2012-12-21 20:13:23','Plan\n\nDo\n\nCheck\n\nAdjust','Take Action to Realize your Talents','','inherit','open','open','','93-revision','','','2012-12-21 20:13:23','2012-12-21 20:13:23','',93,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/93-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(95,1,'2012-12-21 20:17:01','2012-12-21 20:17:01','Don\'t recreate the wheel\r\n\r\nDetermine what is important\r\n\r\nArticulate what you need to do to achieve your dreams\r\n\r\nSet measureable markers (leading indicators)\r\n\r\nUse the data you generate to assess your progress\r\n\r\nMake adjustments\r\n\r\nShare with your sponsors and supporters','Use your Data to Get you There','','draft','open','open','vimbli','use-your-data-to-get-you-there','','','2013-05-30 13:30:01','2013-05-30 13:30:01','',0,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/?page_id=95',0,'page','',0),(96,1,'2012-12-21 20:16:16','2012-12-21 20:16:16','Don\'t recreate the wheel\n\nDetermine what is important\n\nArticulate what you need to do to achieve your dreams\n\nSet measureable markers (leading indicators)\n\nUse the data you generate to assess your progress\n\nMake ad','Use your Data to Get you There','','inherit','open','open','','95-revision','','','2012-12-21 20:16:16','2012-12-21 20:16:16','',95,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/95-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(97,1,'2012-12-21 20:20:33','2012-12-21 20:20:33','Difference between a Sponsor and a Supporter\r\n\r\nYou need both\r\n\r\nYou need to be both\r\n\r\nSponsor:  Do, Get\r\n\r\nSupporter:  Do, See/ Feel\r\n\r\nHow to build?\r\n\r\n- Ask\r\n\r\n- Share goals, get buy-in\r\n\r\n- Establish cadence and expectations\r\n\r\n- Follow through\r\n\r\n- \"All Weather\" / All Seasons ... in different shapes and forms','Build a Net of Sponsors and Supporters','','draft','open','open','vimbli','build-a-net-of-sponsors-and-supporters','','','2013-05-30 13:30:01','2013-05-30 13:30:01','',0,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/?page_id=97',0,'page','',0),(98,1,'2012-12-21 20:20:13','2012-12-21 20:20:13','Difference between a Sponsor and a Supporter\n\nYou need both\n\nYou need to be both\n\nSponsor:  Do, Get\n\nSupporter:  Do, See/ Feel\n\nHow to build?\n\n- Ask\n\n- Share goals, get buy-in\n\n- Establish cadence and expectations\n\n- Follow through\n\n- \"All Weather\" / All Seasons','Build a Net of Sponsors and Supporters','','inherit','open','open','','97-revision','','','2012-12-21 20:20:13','2012-12-21 20:20:13','',97,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/97-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(99,1,'2012-12-21 20:23:39','2012-12-21 20:23:39','Same skills work in other life situations\r\n\r\nWork is just a small part of you ... don\'t let it become you.\r\n\r\nContinue to explore who you are.  Set your horizons and build your net of Sponsors / Supports for you and for different aspects of your life.\r\n\r\nContact us for customized solutions and/ or coaching.','Take \"Onboarding\" Beyond the Job','','draft','open','open','vimbli','take-onboarding-beyond-the-job','','','2013-05-30 13:30:01','2013-05-30 13:30:01','',0,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/?page_id=99',0,'page','',0),(100,1,'2012-12-21 20:23:10','2012-12-21 20:23:10','Same skills work in other life situations\n\nWork is just a small part of you ... don\'t let it become you.\n\nContinue to explore who you are.  Set your horizons and build your net of Sponsors / Supports for you and for different aspects of your life.\n\nContact us for customized solutions and/ or personal coaching.','Take \"Onboarding\" Beyond the Job','','inherit','open','open','','99-revision','','','2012-12-21 20:23:10','2012-12-21 20:23:10','',99,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/99-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(101,1,'2012-12-21 20:24:40','2012-12-21 20:24:40','Same skills work in other life situations\n\nWork is just a small part of you ... don\'t let it become you.\n\nContinue to explore who you are.  Set your horizons and build your net of Sponsors / Supports for you and for different aspects of your life.\n\nContact us for customized solutions and/ or coaching.','Take \"Onboarding\" Beyond the Job','','inherit','open','open','','99-autosave','','','2012-12-21 20:24:40','2012-12-21 20:24:40','',99,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/99-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(102,1,'2012-12-21 20:12:18','2012-12-21 20:12:18','Know where you are coming from\r\n\r\nKnow where you want to go\r\n\r\nKnow what this current \"moment\" contributes to the journey\r\n\r\nKnow your sponsors and share your goals with them\r\n\r\nKnow your support and share your goals with them\r\n\r\nBe deliberate your your actions\r\n\r\nEnjoy the moment','Keys to Success in Your New Role (... really for most \"NEW\" situations)','','inherit','open','open','','89-revision-3','','','2012-12-21 20:12:18','2012-12-21 20:12:18','',89,'http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/89-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(238,1,'2013-04-15 01:36:42','2013-04-15 01:36:42','[caption id=\"attachment_230\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\" wp-image-230 \" title=\"Personal Goals - Survey\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Personal-Goals.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"263\" /> From the Vimbli Survey: Words used to describe personal plans[/caption]\r\n\r\nWe will begin analyzing responses from the \"What Mattered Most\" onboarding <a title=\"New Job Success Survey\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/NewJobSuccess\" target=\"_blank\">survey</a> on April 15.\r\n\r\nYou have the opportunity to influence the report structure. Below is the working structure for the report:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Survey background and objectives</li>\r\n	<li> Overview of how individuals approached and experienced role transitions:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Personal Plan</li>\r\n	<li>Influencer Insights</li>\r\n	<li>Values</li>\r\n	<li>Strengths</li>\r\n	<li>Performance and engagement</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Assessment of the most valuable elements of supporting a successful transition </span></li>\r\n	<li>Potential actions for employer and employee</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Demographics and survey approach</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 15.555556297302246px; line-height: 26.666667938232422px;\">What do you like? What is missing? Let us know what information you\'re interested in knowing as it relates to managing career transitions and onboarding by commenting below or emailing your questions via the contact options.  </span></div>\r\nIf you would like to receive a summary of the survey results, please <a title=\"Complete the New Job Success Now!\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/NewJobSuccess\" target=\"_blank\">complete the survey</a> and provide your email address.','Want to shape the survey report? This is your chance!','','inherit','open','open','','229-revision-7','','','2013-04-15 01:36:42','2013-04-15 01:36:42','',229,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/229-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(278,1,'2013-05-01 00:31:30','2013-05-01 00:31:30','One in four workers typically make a significant career change every year. The number is probably not much different in your company or group.\r\n\r\nMany companies are investing heavily in onboarding and orientation programs.  The impact of these efforts on the overall performance of the company and the aggregate engagement of the group is typically positive.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately the performance profile and individual experience are not necessarily impacted by the programs.\r\n\r\nWhy?  Most of the programs are designed from the employers perspective, and focus on the company rather than the person being onboarded into the new role.\r\n\r\nIf you believe successful employees are key to your business success you should consider profiling the onboarding experience in your company.\r\n\r\nThe questions you\'ll be able to answer with the survey results are\r\n\r\nDo our employees recognize the programs we provide as an effort to support their development and success?\r\n\r\nWhat drives performance differences between our best performers and the rest of our employees?\r\n\r\nWhere should we invest in our programs to add the most value to our employees?\r\n\r\nAs with most surveys the survey results will provide you with information to explore in more detail, and you will be in a position to make better decisions related to your efforts to support the development and individual success of your employees.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in a the survey for your group or company contact us with some information.','3 Reasons to complete the Vimbli survey','','inherit','open','open','','276-revision-2','','','2013-05-01 00:31:30','2013-05-01 00:31:30','',276,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/276-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(346,1,'2013-06-07 20:43:34','2013-06-07 20:43:34','&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Quick start guide for beta users\" href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-3-Steps-to-get-started.docx\" target=\"_blank\">Vimbli 3 Steps to get started</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','3 Steps to Get Started (Beta Users)','','publish','open','open','','getting-started','','','2013-06-11 16:13:24','2013-06-11 16:13:24','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/?page_id=346',0,'page','',0),(276,1,'2013-05-01 01:34:46','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<strong>The questions you\'ll be able to answer with the survey results are:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Do our employees recognize the programs we provide as an effort to support their development and success?</li>\r\n	<li>What drives performance differences between our best performers and the rest of our employees?</li>\r\n	<li>Where should we invest in our programs to add the most value to our employees?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Why is it important to understand the employee behavior, experience and needs?</strong>\r\n\r\nOne in four workers typically make a significant career change every year. The number is probably not much different in your company or group.\r\n\r\nMany companies are investing heavily in onboarding and orientation programs.  The impact of these efforts on overall performance of the company and the aggregate engagement of the group is typically positive.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately the performance profile and individual experience are not necessarily impacted by the programs.\r\n\r\nWhy?  Most of the programs are designed from the employers perspective, and focus on the company rather than the person being onboarded into the new role.\r\n\r\nIf you believe successful employees are key to your business success you should consider profiling the onboarding experience in your company.  If you are interested in a custom report from your company let us know via the link below.\r\n\r\n[contact-form subject=\'[Vimbli Survey Request Get back to them with an answer ... \'][contact-field label=\'Name\' type=\'text\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Email\' type=\'email\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Website and/ or company name\' type=\'text\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Number of employees to survey\' type=\'text\'/][contact-field label=\'Why do you want the survey for your company?\' type=\'text\'/][/contact-form]','3 Reasons to complete the Vimbli survey','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-05-01 01:34:46','2013-05-01 01:34:46','',0,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?p=276',0,'post','',0),(291,1,'2013-05-28 19:14:16','2013-05-28 19:14:16','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Vimbli-Changing-Onboarding-Odds-Survey-Results-May-2013.pdf\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-320\" title=\"Vimbli Report May 2013\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Vimbli-report-cover-224x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"224\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This report summarizes the early results from the Vimbli Onboarding survey.  You can take part in the research by sharing your latest professional transition in the survey.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We hope the report will help you as you navigate life\'s transitions.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Download your copy now:  <a href=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Vimbli-Changing-Onboarding-Odds-Survey-Results-May-2013.pdf\">Changing Onboarding Odds May 2013</a></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Your feedback is most welcome.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Vimbli Onboarding Report','','publish','open','open','','vimbli-onboarding-report','','','2013-06-01 16:08:30','2013-06-01 16:08:30','',0,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?page_id=291',0,'page','',0),(277,1,'2013-05-01 00:30:57','2013-05-01 00:30:57','One in four workers typically make a significant career change every year. The number is probably not much different in your company or group.\n\nMany companies are investing heavily in onboarding and orientation programs.  The impact of these efforts on the overall performance of the company and the aggregate engagement of the group is typically positive.\n\nUnfortunately the performance profile and individual experience are not necessarily impacted by the programs.\n\nWhy?  Most of the programs are designed from the employers perspective, and focus on the company rather than the person being onboarded into the new role.\n\nIf you believe successful employees are key to your business success you should consider profiling the onboarding experience in your company.\n\nThe questions you\'ll be able to answer with the survey results are\n\nDo our employees recognize the programs we provide as an effort to support their development and success?\n\nWhat drives performance differences between our best performers and the rest of our employees?\n\nWhere should we invest in our programs to add the most value to our employees?\n\nAs with most surveys the survey results will provide you with information to explore in more detail, and you will be in a position to make better decisions related to your efforts to support the development and individual success of your employees.\n\nIf you are interested in a the survey for your group or company contact','3 Reasons to complete the Vimbli survey','','inherit','open','open','','276-revision','','','2013-05-01 00:30:57','2013-05-01 00:30:57','',276,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/276-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(210,1,'2013-04-07 23:00:37','2013-04-07 23:00:37','','First Minutes Count','','inherit','open','open','','img_9850','','','2013-04-07 23:00:37','2013-04-07 23:00:37','',208,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_9850.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(209,1,'2013-04-07 22:53:47','2013-04-07 22:53:47','One of the core Vimbli value propositions is \"new hire ownership\" of the transition.  We believe the individual is best positioned to execute the transition.  The company can support, but the individual needs to step-up and own the transition.\n\nRecent research published in Working Knowledge confirms the focus on the individual as an important driver of a successful onboarding.\n\nIn <a title=\"The First Minutes Count - HBS Working Knowledge\" href=\"http://hbswk.hbs.edu/item/7193.html?wknews=04032013\" target=\"_blank\"><em>First Minutes are Critical in New-Employee Orientation</em></a> Carmen Noble shares new research by Daniel M. Cable, Francesca Gino, and Bradley R. Staats.<strong></strong>\n\nHere is a short summary:  Many believe the first couple of months are key to new hire performance and engagement.  The research indicates companies are focusing too much on \"them\" the company and not enough on the new hire.   Most of the message in the first couple of days and weeks are about the company this the company that. The research found clear benefits to focusing on the individual in the first 15 minutes.  Read the full article for  details on how Wipro determine the individual focus results in more than 25% better retention than the traditional company focused program.\n\nThe <a title=\"The First Minutes Count - HBS Working Knowledge\" href=\"http://hbswk.hbs.edu/item/7193.html?wknews=04032013\" target=\"_blank\">full article</a> is available in Working Knowledge, an online Harvard Business School publication.\n\n<em>The researchers are currently expanding the research.  If your company is interested in being part of a field study please write to Francesca Gino directly at <a href=\"mailto:fgino@hbs.edu\">fgino@hbs.edu</a>.</em>\n\n&nbsp;','The First Minutes Count (Harvard Research)','','inherit','open','open','','208-revision','','','2013-04-07 22:53:47','2013-04-07 22:53:47','',208,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/208-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(149,2,'2013-02-18 06:49:41','2013-02-18 06:49:41','[wpp attribute=\"value\"]','Most read blog topics','','draft','open','open','','most-read-blog-topics-2','','','2013-05-30 13:30:01','2013-05-30 13:30:01','',0,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?page_id=149',0,'page','',0),(150,2,'2013-02-18 06:49:08','2013-02-18 06:49:08','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','open','','149-revision','','','2013-02-18 06:49:08','2013-02-18 06:49:08','',149,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/149-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(151,2,'2013-02-18 06:53:13','2013-02-18 06:53:13','[wpp attribute=\"value\"]','Most read blog topics','','inherit','open','open','','149-autosave','','','2013-02-18 06:53:13','2013-02-18 06:53:13','',149,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/149-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(152,1,'2012-12-11 12:02:57','2012-12-11 12:02:57','Just to see if it works.\r\n\r\nThis is a link <a title=\"Try me now!\" href=\"http://vimbli.com\" target=\"_blank\">THIS</a> to vimbil.com, let\'s see if it works.\r\n\r\nand here goes <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">a list with numbering</span></strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>one</li>\r\n	<li>two</li>\r\n	<li>three</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAnd what will a piece of writing be without bullet points?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Not much</li>\r\n	<li>Great reading</li>\r\n	<li>English lit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAdding the mandatory picture below this text line.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/weekly-graph.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-81\" title=\"weekly graph\" src=\"http://75.125.190.162:7427/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/weekly-graph.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"478\" height=\"623\" /></a>','Test','','inherit','open','open','','80-revision-6','','','2012-12-11 12:02:57','2012-12-11 12:02:57','',80,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?p=152',0,'revision','',0),(153,1,'2013-02-18 23:00:54','2013-02-18 23:00:54','Progress and personal growth does not happen without transitions.\n\nOften these transitions are traumatic.  A new job, a new city, a new company, a new relationship …\n\nNo one transition looks the same, but successful transitions have common elements.  A successful transition requires a lot of effort and focus, but there are three common elements:\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>A shared vision</strong> of what success looks like:  Are you building cathedral, building a shack or pitching a tent.  Your answer will impact everything you do.  If you don’t have an answer you’ll probably need to buckle up for a bumpy ride ‘til you find the vision, and find the sponsor who shares the vision with you.</li>\n	<li>The <strong>building blocks</strong>:  Something worthwhile needs you to do a few things, and to do the things well.  What the things are often differ, but in most cases a transition requires building and maintaining relationships.</li>\n	<li>Regular <strong>reviews and adjustments</strong>:  Few plans actually work out as planned.  Hence the name.  Taking stock of your progress and working with your sponsor (who shares the vision) to make adjustments are key components of executing a transition.  Without the explicit commitment to do the reviews and adjustments you should not waste time on #1 and #2.  Go and buy a lottery ticket instead.</li>\n</ol>\nYou read this and it sounds black and white you need to figure out where you want to add your own color.  The elements identified give only the starting point for you to create your own transition. You have to make adjustments to fit your personality and capabilities, and also align with the company culture and the immediate business needs.\n\nIn future posts we’ll cover the elements in detail and also discuss how to personalize the approach to fit you and your situation.\n\nIn the meantime – What is your secret to a successful transition? If you have different tips for different transitions feel free to share.','Pursuing the value in transitions','','inherit','open','open','','80-revision-7','','','2013-02-18 23:00:54','2013-02-18 23:00:54','',80,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?p=153',0,'revision','',0),(154,1,'2013-02-18 23:01:12','2013-02-18 23:01:12','Progress and personal growth does not happen without transitions.\r\n\r\nOften these transitions are traumatic.  A new job, a new city, a new company, a new relationship …\r\n\r\nNo one transition looks the same, but successful transitions have common elements.  A successful transition requires a lot of effort and focus, but there are three common elements:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>A shared vision</strong> of what success looks like:  Are you building cathedral, building a shack or pitching a tent.  Your answer will impact everything you do.  If you don’t have an answer you’ll probably need to buckle up for a bumpy ride ‘til you find the vision, and find the sponsor who shares the vision with you.</li>\r\n	<li>The <strong>building blocks</strong>:  Something worthwhile needs you to do a few things, and to do the things well.  What the things are often differ, but in most cases a transition requires building and maintaining relationships.</li>\r\n	<li>Regular <strong>reviews and adjustments</strong>:  Few plans actually work out as planned.  Hence the name.  Taking stock of your progress and working with your sponsor (who shares the vision) to make adjustments are key components of executing a transition.  Without the explicit commitment to do the reviews and adjustments you should not waste time on #1 and #2.  Go and buy a lottery ticket instead.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nYou read this and it sounds black and white you need to figure out where you want to add your own color.  The elements identified give only the starting point for you to create your own transition. You have to make adjustments to fit your personality and capabilities, and also align with the company culture and the immediate business needs.\r\n\r\nIn future posts we’ll cover the elements in detail and also discuss how to personalize the approach to fit you and your situation.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime – What is your secret to a successful transition? If you have different tips for different transitions feel free to share.','Pursuing Transitions','','inherit','open','open','','80-revision-8','','','2013-02-18 23:01:12','2013-02-18 23:01:12','',80,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?p=154',0,'revision','',0),(156,1,'2012-12-07 15:26:46','2012-12-07 15:26:46','<a href=\"http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/images.jpeg\"><img class=\"wp-image-5 aligncenter\" title=\"images\" src=\"http://172.24.0.9:9953/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/images.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"158\" height=\"149\" /></a>Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!<strong>Lorem Ipsum</strong> is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Lorem Ipsum has been the industry\'s standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book. It has survived not only five centuries, but also the leap into electronic typesetting, remaining essentially unchanged</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">one</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">two</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">three</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Go and look at <a title=\"Instaplan\" href=\"http://www.instaplan.me/\" target=\"_blank\">this</a> for a source to solve any planning problem.</p>','Hello world!','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision-5','','','2012-12-07 15:26:46','2012-12-07 15:26:46','',1,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?p=156',0,'revision','',0),(187,1,'2013-03-29 16:31:50','2013-03-29 16:31:50','Vimbli exists to help you be more successful.\r\n\r\nOur goal is to increase your knowledge of yourself by being a partner on your life journey.  As you go through life there will be many transitions.  Our first solution addresses corporate transitions (think new job, new company, new boss).\r\n\r\nThe Vimbli solution uses your strengths, values and overall life goals as the starting point to navigate any transition.   Each transition is viewed as a learning opportunity, and is structured to allow you to achieve a successful outcome and to deepen your knowledge of yourself.\r\n\r\nWe have created an straightforward planning and execution framework:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Start with a view of what success looks like</li>\r\n	<li>Recruit a sponsor for your \"endeavour\", and share your view of success (Optional, but highly recommended)</li>\r\n	<li>Convert the \"success\" into the activities and relationships that will increase the probability of a successful outcome</li>\r\n	<li>Review progress and make adjustments throughout the transition (with your sponsor, as needed)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThese 4 elements are deceptively simple on paper, but extremely difficult in practice.  In order to make it as easy as possible we have developed a solution that automates most of the data capture and visualization.\r\n\r\nAt the core Vimbli integrates securely with your calendar, email and address book.  Currently we have Google (gmail and Google Apps) covered, we are working to add Microsoft Exchange.  In future we intend to add voice, IM and SMS as well.\r\n\r\nFor different roles Vimbli allows templates to give you a start to plan your our transition.  There is no short-cut on this piece you need to do the work to define what you want out the mission, what you will do to get it, and share the plan with your sponsor.\r\n\r\nCommunication with your sponsor is streamlined using personalized emails with your activity and goal information.  You own the update.  Before sharing it with your sponsor you have the opportunity to make edits to the content.  Yes you can add and delete.  What you share is your decision.\r\n\r\nWe have created Vimbli with you in mind.   The application will most likely live in the enterprise, but our intend is to serve individuals who want to live life to the full.\r\n\r\nThat is why we picked the name Vimbli.  A play on \"vim and vigor\", meaning \"a zest for life\".  We wanted to capture the energy involved in transitions and personal growth.  We are looking forward to have you on the journey with us.\r\n\r\nWhat would you like to see in a solution like Vimbli?  Let us know.','What is Vimbli?','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision-8','','','2013-03-29 16:31:50','2013-03-29 16:31:50','',1,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/1-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(175,1,'2013-03-28 22:17:56','2013-03-28 22:17:56','','iStock_000021386717Large-003','','inherit','open','open','','istock_000021386717large-003','','','2013-03-28 22:17:56','2013-03-28 22:17:56','',106,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/iStock_000021386717Large-003.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(157,1,'2013-02-18 23:28:18','2013-02-18 23:28:18','Progress and personal growth does not happen without transitions.\r\n\r\nOften these transitions are traumatic.  A new job, a new city, a new company, a new relationship …\r\n\r\nNo one transition looks the same, but successful transitions have common elements.  A successful transition requires a lot of effort and focus, but there are three common elements:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>A shared vision</strong> of what success looks like:  Are you building cathedral, building a shack or pitching a tent.  Your answer will impact everything you do.  If you don’t have an answer you’ll probably need to buckle up for a bumpy ride ‘til you find the vision, and find the sponsor who shares the vision with you.</li>\r\n	<li>The <strong>building blocks</strong>:  Something worthwhile needs you to do a few things, and to do the things well.  What the things are often differ, but in most cases a transition requires building and maintaining relationships.</li>\r\n	<li>Regular <strong>reviews and adjustments</strong>:  Few plans actually work out as planned.  Hence the name.  Taking stock of your progress and working with your sponsor (who shares the vision) to make adjustments are key components of executing a transition.  Without the explicit commitment to do the reviews and adjustments you should not waste time on #1 and #2.  Go and buy a lottery ticket instead.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nYou read this and it sounds black and white you need to figure out where you want to add your own color.  The elements identified give only the starting point for you to create your own transition. You have to make adjustments to fit your personality and capabilities, and also align with the company culture and the immediate business needs.\r\n\r\nIn future posts we’ll cover the elements in detail and also discuss how to personalize the approach to fit you and your situation.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime – What is your secret to a successful transition? If you have different tips for different transitions feel free to share.','Pursuing the value in transitions','','inherit','open','open','','80-revision-9','','','2013-02-18 23:28:18','2013-02-18 23:28:18','',80,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?p=157',0,'revision','',0),(162,1,'2013-05-30 13:30:02','0000-00-00 00:00:00','To test if the addin works.  I hope so.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"wysija-register\"></div>\r\n&nbsp;','Wysija - Test','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-05-30 13:30:02','2013-05-30 13:30:02','',0,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?page_id=162',0,'page','',0),(163,1,'2013-03-04 19:18:18','2013-03-04 19:18:18','To test if the addin works.  I hope so.\n\n&nbsp;\n<div class=\"wysija-register\"></div>\n&nbsp;','Wysija - Test','','inherit','open','open','','162-revision','','','2013-03-04 19:18:18','2013-03-04 19:18:18','',162,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/?p=163',0,'revision','',0),(292,1,'2013-05-28 19:09:15','2013-05-28 19:09:15','','Changing Onboarding Odds May 2013','','inherit','open','open','','vimbli-changing-onboarding-odds-survey-results-may-2013','','','2013-05-28 19:09:15','2013-05-28 19:09:15','',291,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/b