d by the programs.\n\nWhy?  Most of the programs are designed from the employers perspective, and focus on the company rather than the person being onboarded into the new role.\n\nIf you believe successful employees are key to your business success you should consider profiling the onboarding experience in your company.  If you are interested in a custom report from your company let us know via the link below.\n\n[contact-form subject=\'[Vimbli Survey Request Get back to them with an answer ... \'][contact-field label=\'Name\' type=\'text\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Email\' type=\'email\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Website and/ or company name\' type=\'text\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Number of employees to survey\' type=\'text\'/][contact-field label=\'Why do you want the survey for your company?\' type=\'text\'/][/contact-form]','3 Reasons to complete the Vimbli survey','','inherit','open','open','','276-revision-6','','','2013-05-01 00:57:35','2013-05-01 00:57:35','',276,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/276-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(279,1,'2013-05-01 00:48:59','2013-05-01 00:48:59','One in four workers typically make a significant career change every year. The number is probably not much different in your company or group.\n\nMany companies are investing heavily in onboarding and orientation programs.  The impact of these efforts on the overall performance of the company and the aggregate engagement of the group is typically positive.\n\nUnfortunately the performance profile and individual experience are not necessarily impacted by the programs.\n\nWhy?  Most of the programs are designed from the employers perspective, and focus on the company rather than the person being onboarded into the new role.\n\nIf you believe successful employees are key to your business success you should consider profiling the onboarding experience in your company.\n\nThe questions you\'ll be able to answer with the survey results ar