vide as an effort to support their development and success?</li>\r\n	<li>What drives performance differences between our best performers and the rest of our employees?</li>\r\n	<li>Where should we invest in our programs to add the most value to our employees?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Why is it important to understand the employee behavior, experience and needs?</strong>\r\n\r\nOne in four workers typically make a significant career change every year. The number is probably not much different in your company or group.\r\n\r\nMany companies are investing heavily in onboarding and orientation programs.  The impact of these efforts on overall performance of the company and the aggregate engagement of the group is typically positive.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately the performance profile and individual experience are not necessarily impacted by the programs.\r\n\r\nWhy?  Most of the programs are designed from the employers perspective, and focus on the company rather than the person being onboarded into the new role.\r\n\r\nIf you believe successful employees are key to your business success you should consider profiling the onboarding experience in your company.  If you are interested in a custom report from your company let us know via the link below.\r\n\r\n[contact-form subject=\'[Vimbli Survey Request Get back to them with an answer ... \'][contact-field label=\'Name\' type=\'text\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Email\' type=\'email\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Website and/ or company name\' type=\'text\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Number of employees to survey\' type=\'text\'/][contact-field label=\'Why do you want the survey for your company?\' type=\'text\'/][/contact-form]','3 Reasons to complete the Vimbli survey','','inherit','open','open','','276-revision-7','','','2013-05-01 01:00:18','2013-05-01 01:00:18','',276,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/276-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(284,1,'2013-04-21 22:30:40','2013-04-21 22:30:40','<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-264\" title=\"Winner\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_8351-002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"364\" />... Nancy Gross!\r\n\r\nThanks to all who completed the survey.   We decided to leave the survey open. Going forward we\'ll draw every 200 responses.\r\n\r\nIf you have not completed the Vimbli survey, you still have a chance to share your last professional change.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"The survey takes less than 5 minutes take it now ...\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/NewJobSuccess\" target=\"_blank\">Take the Vimbli survey ...</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','And the Winner is ... ','','inherit','open','open','','253-revision-11','','','2013-04-21 22:30:40','2013-04-21 22:30:40','',253,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/253-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(285,1,'2013-05-01 01:36:24','2013-05-01 01:36:24','<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-264\" title=\"Winner\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/IMG_8351-002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"364\" />... Nancy Gross!\r\n\r\nThanks to all who completed the survey.   We decided to leave the survey open. Going forward we\'ll draw every 200 responses.\r\n\r\nIf you have not completed the Vimbli survey, you still have a chance to share your last professional change.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"The survey takes less than 5 minutes take it now ...\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/NewJobSuccess\" target=\"_blank\">Take the Vimbli survey ...</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','And the Winner is ... ','','inherit','open','open','','253-revision-12','','','2013-05-01 01:36:24','2013-05-01 01:36:24','',253,'http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/253-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(419,1,'2013-07-04 17:15:09','2013-07-04 17:15:09','<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-420\" title=\"Portugese soldiers - WW1\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Portugese-soldiers-WW1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"415\" />\r\n\r\nLife happens and sometimes we have to wait.  Either for something to happen, somebody to show up, or just for personal inspiration.\r\n\r\nI found that if I take an active approach to waiting the time is often very valuable, and in most cases enjoyable.  When I don\'t take an active approach.  Well, let\'s just say the outcomes are often sub-optimal ...\r\n\r\nI take a 4 step approach to make the most of waiting time. Below are the four.  Let me know what you do to make the most the time you spend waiting.\r\n\r\n<strong>1. Know why you are waiting ... </strong>\r\n\r\nThis sounds obvious, but in many cases waiting is an option.  Instead of waiting for the bus you can walk to the next bus stop, that cut back the wait time and add to your exercise time.  In some cases you are stuck with some waiting time.  If you are at the DMV it could be a long and frustrating wait ...\r\n\r\n<strong>2.  Get to know fellow \"waiters\" ...</strong>\r\n\r\nMost likely you are not waiting alone.  Take the time to get to know some of the people waiting with you.  This is the step I am most likely to skip, but I often find this to be the most rewarding use of my time.  Keep in mind s/he is just as frustrated by the wait as you, and if not it will be interesting to know why they are not annoyed by the wait.\r\n\r\n<strong>3.  Take action on things on your list ... </strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Your wait could be short, in which case you feel you cannot do anything productive.  Or it could be long, but you cannot work on that work sensitive material.  There could be several excuses not to take actions.  If you have a ready list of things you can do in various situations the excuses become less relevant, and it is easier to break free from inertia.</span>\r\n\r\nDon\'t know where to start?  A few ideas\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Less than 5 minutes?   Send a note to someone celebrating a birthday, send an invitation for coffee to a friend, jot down your thoughts related to a meeting later in the day, clean-up email subscriptions, ... </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">30 minutes?  Draft a new document, review a proposal, clean-up your inbox, carry a couple of stamped postcards with you and send friends written notes, make phone calls ... </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">More than an hour?  Mix-and-match the 30 minute elements, with shorter elements.   </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 15.555556297302246px; line-height: 26.666667938232422px;\">Note the focus on creating and sharing.  Avoid \"consumption\" of content.  </span></div>\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 15.555556297302246px; line-height: 26.666667938232422px;\">4.  Consume content, including people watching ... </span></strong>\r\n\r\nLastly, after I have exhausted my options in 1, 2 and 3 I\'ll switch to consumption of content.  People watching, reading, catching up on emails and LinkedIn, and if I really have time ... check Facebook.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">What do you do when you have to wait?</span>\r\n\r\nHennie\r\n\r\nFounder, Vimbli\r\n\r\nPhoto:  Courtesy <a title=\"Portugese Soldiers WW1\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/nlscotland/4699288263/\" target=\"_blank\">National Library of Scotland</a>, via Flickr.  <span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Original title: \'OFFICIAL PHOTOGRAPHS TAKEN ON THE BRITISH WESTERN FRONT. Portuguese in the trenches. A letter home.</span>','Four Keys to Better Waiting','','publish','open','open','','four-keys-to-better-waiting','','','2013-07-04 19:01:41','2013-07-04 19:01:41','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/?p=419',0,'post','',1),(299,1,'2013-05-31 14:48:20','2013-05-31 14:48:20','&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_307\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"706\"]<img class=\" wp-image-307    \" title=\"Son &amp; Dad - Resting. Together.\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/6733_109417881614_5502440_n-001.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"706\" height=\"524\" /> Junior &amp; Senior<br />Isilimela, Transkei/ Eastern Cape, South Africa<br />(early 1973?)[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I am getting ready for a big personal transition: Manhood to Dadhood.  Simone and I are expecting our first in 4 weeks.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">How did you navigate the man to dad transition?  Please share your transition experience in the comment section below or this <a title=\"Share your man to dad transition!\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/VIMBLIDMT\" target=\"_blank\">survey</a>. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Vimbli exists to help individuals and groups make the most of big life transitions.  </span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">To help me make deliberate, informed choices (and to test Vimbli outside the corporate environment) I want to set up a Vimbli \"Mission\" for my \"dad\" transition.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Your experience during the dad transition will be most helpful as I shape my plan.   I am aware that the plan is not going to hold up, but I do subscribe to Eisenhower\'s words:</span>\r\n\r\n<em>Plans are nothing; planning is everything.</em>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Please use this <a title=\"Complete the Man to Dad Survey\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/VIMBLIDMT\" target=\"_blank\">link</a> to get to the survey or respond in the comments.  If you can share this request with dads in your life it will mean a lot to me.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Thanks</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a title=\"More about Hennie\" href=\"www.linkedin.com/in/henniestrydom/\" target=\"_blank\">Hennie</a> - Dad-to-be, and Vimbli founder</span>','Calling all fathers - How would you describe your Dad transition?','','publish','open','open','','man-to-dadhood-transition-a-personal-journey','','','2013-05-31 14:51:38','2013-05-31 14:51:38','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/?p=299',0,'post','',0),(300,1,'2013-05-29 14:39:11','2013-05-29 14:39:11','','Man- to Dadhood transition - A personal journey','','inherit','open','open','','299-revision','','','2013-05-29 14:39:11','2013-05-29 14:39:11','',299,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/299-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(301,1,'2013-05-29 14:42:59','2013-05-29 14:42:59','<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-177\" title=\"logo-1024\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/logo-1024-300x146.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"146\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Man- to Dadhood transition - A personal journey','','inherit','open','open','','299-revision-2','','','2013-05-29 14:42:59','2013-05-29 14:42:59','',299,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/299-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(302,1,'2013-05-31 14:54:49','2013-05-31 14:54:49','&nbsp;\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_307\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"650\"]<img class=\" wp-image-307     \" title=\"Son &amp; Dad - Resting. Together.\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/6733_109417881614_5502440_n-001.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"650\" height=\"524\" /> Junior &amp; Senior<br />Isilimela, Transkei/ Eastern Cape, South Africa<br />(early 1973?)[/caption]\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I am getting ready for a big personal transition: Manhood to Dadhood.  Simone and I are expecting our first in 4 weeks.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">How did you navigate the man to dad transition?  Please share your transition experience in the comment section below or this <a title=\"Share your man to dad transition!\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/VIMBLIDMT\" target=\"_blank\">survey</a>. </span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Vimbli exists to help individuals and groups make the most of big life transitions.  </span><span s