t','open','open','','346-autosave','','','2013-06-11 16:14:30','2013-06-11 16:14:30','',346,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/346-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(349,1,'2013-06-07 20:43:34','2013-06-07 20:43:34','Content to follow','Getting Started','','inherit','open','open','','346-revision-2','','','2013-06-07 20:43:34','2013-06-07 20:43:34','',346,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/346-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(353,1,'2013-06-10 20:26:21','2013-06-10 20:26:21','&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-3-Steps-to-get-started.docx\">Vimbli 3 Steps to get started</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','3 Steps to Get Started (Beta Users)','','inherit','open','open','','346-revision-5','','','2013-06-10 20:26:21','2013-06-10 20:26:21','',346,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/346-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(352,1,'2013-06-10 20:24:32','2013-06-10 20:24:32','<a href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-3-Steps-to-get-started.docx\">Vimbli 3 Steps to get started</a>','3 Steps to Get Started (Beta Users)','','inherit','open','open','','346-revision-4','','','2013-06-10 20:24:32','2013-06-10 20:24:32','',346,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/346-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(355,1,'2013-06-10 20:26:30','2013-06-10 20:26:30','&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-3-Steps-to-get-started.docx\">Vimbli 3 Steps to get started</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','3 Steps to Get Started (Beta Users)','','inherit','open','open','','346-revision-6','','','2013-06-10 20:26:30','2013-06-10 20:26:30','',346,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/346-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(351,1,'2013-06-10 19:51:21','2013-06-10 19:51:21','Follow the link in the email\r\n\r\nUse the Google interface to link your data (note this link happens in Google and Vimbli will never have your Google login info)\r\n\r\nUpdate your password\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nComplete a reflection (see menu in the left panel)\r\n\r\nSelect to start a  Mission.\r\n\r\nYou’ll see a form with elements of your mission plan.\r\n\r\nDO NOT complete the following in  your first mission:\r\n\r\nAdd a sponsor\r\n\r\nAdd Connection goals\r\n\r\nDO complete the following:\r\n\r\nName of the mission\r\n\r\nStart / End date\r\n\r\nDescription of the mission (context)\r\n\r\nSuccess metrics\r\n\r\nKeys to success … here just define 1 or 2 “keys”.  Think of the most important 2-3 activities in your “plan” and add hours per period (weekly, monthly or for the full mission) , specify a start / end date if different from misison, and customize the keywords you want Vimbli to consider in your linked Google calendar.\r\n\r\nUse Vimbli for 2-3 days to get the hang of the solution\r\n\r\nDecide who you’ll ask to be your sponsor for your mission\r\n\r\nUpdate your mission with sponsor and connections\r\n\r\nGuide to the Menu in the left bar:\r\n\r\nJourney (takes you to your dashboard view showing your progress on your journey)\r\n\r\nReflection (takes you to the reflection form)\r\n\r\nRefine (takes you to your mission options, timeline, connections and foundational set-up)\r\n\r\nResearch (this is background on Vimbli and the reasoning behind building the solution\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','3 Steps to Get Started (Beta Users)','','inherit','open','open','','346-revision-3','','','2013-06-10 19:51:21','2013-06-10 19:51:21','',346,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/346-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(354,1,'2013-06-11 16:11:46','2013-06-11 16:11:46','','Vimbli 3 Steps to get started','','inherit','open','open','','vimbli-3-steps-to-get-started','','','2013-06-11 16:11:46','2013-06-11 16:11:46','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-3-Steps-to-get-started.docx',0,'attachment','application/msword',0),(356,1,'2013-06-14 18:43:30','2013-06-14 18:43:30','Not the operating system, just the Vimbli App.  We officially stopped maintaining the application in the Play Store.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_357\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-357\" title=\"Sign up for the beta waitlist\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-App-screenshot-of-store-300x255.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"255\" /></a> Screenshot of the Play Store entry for the Vimbli Android application. We ceased all development and maintenance of the application. You can sign up for the web-based Beta waitlist ... :)[/caption]\r\n\r\nThanks to all who downloaded the application.  Your feedback shaped the web-based solution we are now testing with beta users.  If you think you\'ll be a great beta user l<a title=\"Sign up for the Beta Waitlist\" href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\" target=\"_blank\">et us know</a>.\r\n\r\nIf you want to use the  most recent Android application (<a title=\"Download the Android App\" href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/feer86bb4rsvhuv/vimbli_v1.06.apk\" target=\"_blank\">v1.06</a>) you can install this file on your Android device.  Please note we are not maintaining this solution.  If it crashes logout and try again.  If that does not solve the issue the issue will stay an issue.  Apologies.','RIP Android','','publish','open','open','','rip-android','','','2013-06-14 21:42:39','2013-06-14 21:42:39','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/?p=356',0,'post','',0),(357,1,'2013-06-14 17:28:27','2013-06-14 17:28:27','','Sign up for the beta waitlist','Screenshot of the Play Store entry for the Vimbli Android application.  We ceased all development and maintenance of the application.  You can sign up for the web-based Beta waitlist ... :) ','inherit','open','open','','vimbli-app-screenshot-of-store','','','2013-06-14 17:28:27','2013-06-14 17:28:27','',356,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-App-screenshot-of-store.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(358,1,'2013-06-14 17:30:41','2013-06-14 17:30:41','Not the operating system, just the Vimbli App.  We stopped maintaining the application in the Play Store.\n\nA thanks to all who downloaded the application.  Your feedback shaped the web based solution we are now testing with beta users.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-357\" title=\"Vimbli - App store front screen shot\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-App-screenshot-of-store-300x255.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"255\" />\n\nIf you want to use the  most recent Android application you can install this file on your Android device.  Please note we are not maintaining the solution any longer.','RIP Android','','inherit','open','open','','356-revision','','','2013-06-14 17:30:41','2013-06-14 17:30:41','',356,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/356-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(359,1,'2013-06-15 17:06:54','2013-06-15 17:06:54','[caption id=\"attachment_384\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-384\" title=\"20130615_094153\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/20130615_094153-1022x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"641\" /> Tip #1: Write your goals down. It is easy to do, and it works![/caption]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Want to reach more of your goals:  Start by writing your goals down.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Read on to learn more.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><a title=\"About - Michael Hyatt\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/about\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Hyatt</a> recently posted a <a title=\"Michael Hyatt Goal Setting 101\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/goal-setting.html\" target=\"_blank\">Goal Setting</a> guide.  If you are good at setting goals and realizing goals it is worth a read.  If you are so-so at achieving your goals it will definitely be a good return on your time to read the article.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">In the post he describes his 5 principles for goal execution:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">keep the goals few in number</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">make the goals <a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SMART_criteria\" target=\"_blank\">SMART</a> (John Richardson <a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" title=\"John\'s SMART worksheet\" href=\"http://personalsuccesstoday.com/goal-setting-worksheet/\" target=\"_blank\">covers</a> SMART goals)</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">write the goals down</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">review frequently</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">share selectively</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Michael\'s post aligns well with the onboarding solution we are <a title=\"Make your transition 80 percent more successful\" href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/\" target=\"_blank\">currently testing</a>.  The focus of the solution is to help people make the most of professional transitions.    This focus requires the Vimbli solution to prioritize the right things over just getting more done.  In every transition there is a set of things that needs to get done, but transitions are crazy and you need to stay nimble and focused on the transition priorities.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Michael refers to a report by <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gail-matthews\">Professor Gail Matthews</a> on factors impacting goal completion.  The research is still in progress, but the initial findings are aligned with core message from the recent Vimbli Onboarding report.  The Vimbli report states people with personal plans are twice as likely to be top performers than those without personal plans. (You can get a copy of the report <a title=\"Signup to get the Vimbli report\" href=\"http://eepurl.com/AkdlH\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Spending some time digging into the <a title=\"Prof Matthews\' Goals Research\" href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gailmatthews/researchsummary2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">initial findings</a> of Matthews research is worth it.  The 3 core findings are listed below.  We used Case 1 as baseline for our impact calculations.  (Case 1:  No written goals, no accountability, no engagement.)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">1.  The <strong>80%</strong> Factor.  <em>Engagement</em>:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates they were more likely to achieve success than those who did not reach out regularly.  (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  7.6  Improvement:  78%!)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">2.  The <strong>50%</strong> Factor. <em>Accountability</em>: Those who made the commitment to someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not. (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  6.41  Improvement:  50% )</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">3.  The <strong>40%</strong> Factor. <em>Written commitment</em>:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Getting someone to support you on your journey (#2), and keeping up with regular updates (#1) are a challenge.  Writing down your goals is much easier (#3).</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Are you already writing down your goals?  Yes? Great!  No? Why not?  If it makes you 40% more likely to achieve the goals ... No excuses. Get started!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Once you have the goals written you can look into a service like <a href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/\" target=\"_blank\">Vimbli</a>.  Vimbli makes Engagement and Accountability easier, but if you don\'t take the first step no solution will help you. </span>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_368\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-368\" title=\"Draft of progress provided by Vimbli\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the automated progress report prepared by Vimbli.<br />(Currently in closed beta.)[/caption]','Write it down ... ','','publish','open','open','','write-it-down','','\nhttp://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/','2013-06-15 17:09:14','2013-06-15 17:09:14','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/?p=359',0,'post','',0),(360,1,'2013-06-14 18:10:15','2013-06-14 18:10:15','Michael Hyatt recently posted a 101 on Goal Setting.  If you are good at setting goals and realizing goals it is worth a read.  If you are so-so at achieving your goals it will definitely be a good return on your time to read the article.\n\nAt Vimbli we are excited about Michael\'s post as it supports the design of the solution we have put in place the help individuals make the most of professional transitions.  More on how Vimbli help support Michael\'s Goal Setting 101 in this post.\n\nIn his post Michael refers to a report on the value of written goals, but he does not get deeper into the report.  The report is aligned with the Vimbli report on professional transitions.  The Vimbli report indicated people with personal plans are twice as likely to be top performers than those without.   The Prof  Gail Matthews reports in the i