port indicated people with personal plans are twice as likely to be top performers than those without.   The Prof  Gail Matthews reports some interesting facts in the initial findings of her research.\n\n1.  Engagement:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates were more likely to achieve success than those who did not reach out regularly.\n\n2.  Accountability: Those who made the commitment to someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not.\n\n3.  Written commitment:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.\n\nGetting someone to support you on your journey, and keeping up with regular updates could both be challenging, but you can write down your goals.  Why not?  If it makes you 50% more likely to achieve the goals ... let\'s get started!\n\n&nbsp;','The value of writing down goals? 50% increase in completion rate!','','inherit','open','open','','359-revision-4','','','2013-06-14 18:21:16','2013-06-14 18:21:16','',359,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/359-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(365,1,'2013-06-14 21:43:45','2013-06-14 21:43:45','Not the operating system, just the Vimbli App.  We officially stopped maintaining the application in the Play Store.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_357\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-357\" title=\"Sign up for the beta waitlist\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-App-screenshot-of-store-300x255.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"255\" /></a> Screenshot of the Play Store entry for the Vimbli Android application. We ceased all development and maintenance of the application. You can sign up for the web-based Beta waitlist ... :)[/caption]\n\nThanks to all who downloaded the application.  Your feedback shaped the web-based solution we are now testing with beta users.  If you think you\'ll be a great beta user l<a title=\"Sign up for the Beta Waitlist\" href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\" target=\"_blank\">et us know</a>.\n\nIf you want to use the  most recent Android application (<a title=\"Download the Android App\" href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/feer86bb4rsvhuv/vimbli_v1.06.apk\" target=\"_blank\">v1.06</a>) you can install this file on your Android device.  Please note we are not maintaining this solution.  If it crashes logout and try again.  If that does not solve the issue the issue will stay an issue.  Apologies.','RIP Android','','inherit','open','open','','356-autosave','','','2013-06-14 21:43:45','2013-06-14 21:43:45','',356,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/356-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(364,1,'2013-06-14 18:42:34','2013-06-14 18:42:34','Not the operating system, just the Vimbli App.  We officially stopped maintaining the application in the Play Store.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_357\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-357\" title=\"Sign up for the beta waitlist\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-App-screenshot-of-store-300x255.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"255\" /></a> Screenshot of the Play Store entry for the Vimbli Android application. We ceased all development and maintenance of the application. You can sign up for the web-based Beta waitlist ... :)[/caption]\n\nA thanks to all who downloaded the application.  Your feedback shaped the web based solution we are now testing with beta users.  If you think you\'ll be a great beta user l<a title=\"Sign up for the Beta Waitlist\" href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\" target=\"_blank\">et us know</a>.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you want to use the  most recent Android application (<a title=\"Download the Android App\" href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/feer86bb4rsvhuv/vimbli_v1.06.apk\" target=\"_blank\">v1.06</a>) you can install this file on your Android device.  Please note we are not maintaining the solution any longer.  If it crashes please logout and try again.  If that does not solve the issue the issue will stay an issue.  Apologies.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_357\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-357\" title=\"Sign up for the beta waitlist\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-App-screenshot-of-store-300x255.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"255\" /></a> Screenshot of the Play Store entry for the Vimbli Android application. We ceased all development and maintenance of the application. You can sign up for the web-based Beta waitlist ... :)[/caption]','RIP Android','','inherit','open','open','','356-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 18:42:34','2013-06-14 18:42:34','',356,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/356-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(366,1,'2013-06-14 18:43:30','2013-06-14 18:43:30','Not the operating system, just the Vimbli App.  We officially stopped maintaining the application in the Play Store.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_357\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-357\" title=\"Sign up for the beta waitlist\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Vimbli-App-screenshot-of-store-300x255.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"255\" /></a> Screenshot of the Play Store entry for the Vimbli Android application. We ceased all development and maintenance of the application. You can sign up for the web-based Beta waitlist ... :)[/caption]\r\n\r\nA thanks to all who downloaded the application.  Your feedback shaped the web based solution we are now testing with beta users.  If you think you\'ll be a great beta user l<a title=\"Sign up for the Beta Waitlist\" href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\" target=\"_blank\">et us know</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you want to use the  most recent Android application (<a title=\"Download the Android App\" href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/feer86bb4rsvhuv/vimbli_v1.06.apk\" target=\"_blank\">v1.06</a>) you can install this file on your Android device.  Please note we are not maintaining this solution any longer.  If it crashes please logout and try again.  If that does not solve the issue the issue will stay an issue.  Apologies.','RIP Android','','inherit','open','open','','356-revision-3','','','2013-06-14 18:43:30','2013-06-14 18:43:30','',356,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/356-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(368,1,'2013-06-15 15:05:08','2013-06-15 15:05:08','Vimbli automates the creation of a progress report by integrating with your calendar and email, and using your personal settings.  You then gets a draft report in your email.  The expectation is for you to edit the report before sharing it with your sponsor(s). ','Draft of progress provided by Vimbli','An example of the automated progress report prepared by Vimbli. \r\n(Currently in closed beta.)','inherit','open','open','','x-progress-draft','','','2013-06-15 15:05:08','2013-06-15 15:05:08','',359,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(369,1,'2013-06-15 15:10:43','2013-06-15 15:10:43','<a title=\"About - Michael Hyatt\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/about\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Hyatt</a> recently posted a 101 on <a title=\"Michael Hyatt Goal Setting 101\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/goal-setting.html\" target=\"_blank\">Goal Setting</a>.  If you are good at setting goals and realizing goals it is worth a read.  If you are so-so at achieving your goals it will definitely be a good return on your time to read the article.\n\nIn his post he describes 5 principles:\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">keep the goals few in number</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">make the goals </span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SMART_criteria\" target=\"_blank\">SMART</a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> (John Richardson </span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" title=\"John\'s SMART worksheet\" href=\"http://personalsuccesstoday.com/goal-setting-worksheet/\" target=\"_blank\">covers</a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> this well)</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">write the goals down</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">review frequently</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">share selectively</span></li>\n</ol>\n<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">At Vimbli we are excited about Michael\'s post as it supports the design of the solution we have put in place the help individuals make the most of professional transitions.  At Vimbli we are not focused on getting more done, our focus is on making the most of life transitions.  In every transition there is a set of things that needs to get done, but transitions are crazy and you need to stay nimble and focused on the priorities.  Both requires a good understanding of the transition and how the transition fits with your overall plan.  </span>\n\nIn his post Michael refers to a report by Professor Gail Matthews on the value of written goals.  The report is aligned with the Vimbli report on professional transitions.  The <a title=\"Vimbli Onboarding Report\" href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-onboarding-report/\" target=\"_blank\">Vimbli report</a> indicated people with personal plans are twice as likely to be top performers than those without.   The Prof  Gail Matthews reports some interesting facts in the <a title=\"Prof Matthews\' Goals Research\" href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gailmatthews/researchsummary2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">initial findings</a> of her research.\n\nThe 3 core themes are listed below.  All impact numbers are the based on the relative increase from the base line.  We took the baseline as case 1 in her group:  Not written down, no accountability, no engagement.\n\n1.  The <strong>80%</strong> Factor.  Engagement:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates were more likely to achieve success than those who did not reach out regularly.  (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  7.6  Improvement:  78%!)\n\n2.  The <strong>50%</strong> Factor. Accountability: Those who made the commitment to someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not. (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  6.41  Improvement:  50% )\n\n3.  The <strong>40%</strong> Factor. Written commitment:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.\n\nGetting someone to support you on your journey, and keeping up with regular updates can be challenging, but you can write down your goals.\n\nWhy not?  If it makes you 40% more likely to achieve the goals ... let\'s get started!\n\nOnce you have the goals written down you can look into a service like Vimbli.  Vimbli does streamline the Engagement and Accountability, but if you don\'t take the first step no solution will help you.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_368\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-368\" title=\"Draft of progress provided by Vimbli\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the automated progress report prepared by Vimbli.<br />(Currently in closed beta.)[/caption]','Goals','','inherit','open','open','','359-revision-5','','','2013-06-15 15:10:43','2013-06-15 15:10:43','',359,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/359-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(370,1,'2013-06-15 15:11:59','2013-06-15 15:11:59','<a title=\"About - Michael Hyatt\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/about\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Hyatt</a> recently posted a 101 on <a title=\"Michael Hyatt Goal Setting 101\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/goal-setting.html\" target=\"_blank\">Goal Setting</a>.  If you are good at setting goals and realizing goals it is worth a read.  If you are so-so at achieving your goals it will definitely be a good return on your time to read the article.\n\nIn his post he describes 5 principles:\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">keep the goals few in number</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">make the goals </span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SMART_criteria\" target=\"_blank\">SMART</a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> (John Richardson </span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" title=\"John\'s SMART worksheet\" href=\"http://personalsuccesstoday.com/goal-setting-worksheet/\" target=\"_blank\">covers</a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> this well)</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">write the goals down</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">review frequently</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">share selectively</span></li>\n</ol>\n<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">At Vimbli we are excited about Michael\'s post as it supports the design of the solution we have put in place the help individuals make the most of professional transitions.  At Vimbli we are not focused on getting more done, our focus is on making the most of life transitions.  In every transition there is a set of things that needs to get done, but transitions are crazy and you need to stay nimble and focused on the priorities.  Both requires a good understanding of the transition and how the transition fits with your overall plan.  </span>\n\nIn his post Michael refers to a report by Professor Gail Matthews on the value of written goals.  The report is aligned with the Vimbli report on professional transitions.  The <a title=\"Vimbli Onboarding Report\" href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-onboarding-report/\" target=\"_blank\">Vimbli report</a> indicated people with personal plans are twice as likely to be top performers than those without.   The Prof  Gail Matthews reports some interesting facts in the <a title=\"Prof Matthews\' Goals Research\" href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gailmatthews/researchsummary2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">initial findings</a> of her research.\n\nThe 3 core themes are listed below.  All impact numbers are the based on the relative increase from the base line.  We took the baseline as case 1 in her group:  Not written down, no accountability, no engagement.\n\n1.  The <strong>80%</strong> Factor.  Engagement:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates were more likely to achieve success than those who did not reach out regularly.  (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  7.6  Improvement:  78%!)\n\n2.  The <strong>50%</strong> Factor. Accountability: Those who made the commitment to someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not. (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  6.41  Improvement:  50% )\n\n3.  The <strong>40%</strong> Factor. Written commitment:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.\n\nGetting someone to support you on your journey, and keeping up with regular updates can be challenging, but you can write down your goals.\n\nWhy not?  If it makes you 40% more likely to achieve the goals ... let\'s get started!\n\nOnce you have the goals written down you can look into a service like Vimbli.  Vimbli does streamline the Engagement and Accountability, but if you don\'t take the first step no solution will help you.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_368\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-368\" title=\"Draft of progress provided by Vimbli\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the automated progress report prepared by Vimbli.<br />(Currently in closed beta.)[/caption]','Are you writing your goals down?','','inherit','open','open','','359-revision-6','','','2013-06-15 15:11:59','2013-06-15 15:11:59','',359,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/359-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(371,1,'2013-06-15 16:29:34','2013-06-15 16:29:34','<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-391\" title=\"Success (photo: Istockphoto.com)\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/iStock_000005449225Large.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"401\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Initial <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gailmatthews/researchsummary2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">findings</a> from <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gail-matthews\" target=\"_blank\">Prof Gail Matthews</a>\' research show that you are more likely to meet your goals if you do certain things.  A lot more likely!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Here are the 3 things the research suggests you should consider for your next your plan or set of goals:</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">1.  The <strong>80%</strong> Factor.  <em>Engagement</em>:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates they were more likely to be successful than those who did not reach out regularly.  (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  7.6  Improvement:  78%!)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">2.  The <strong>50%</strong> Factor. <em>Accountability</em>: Those who shared their goals with someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not. (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  6.41  Improvement:  50% )</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">3.  The <strong>40%</strong> Factor. <em>Written commitment</em>:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The findings align well with the mythical 3% success research by Harvard Business School (HBS) or Yale.   You can pick the most prestigious one when you quote the \"research\" at the next cocktail party or tailgate ;) .  The myth goes like this: 3% of the graduating class (1953 or 1979?) had written goals. Twenty (or 10) years later the 3% earned 10 times what the \"no clear goals\"-group did ... well, it is just a myth (<a title=\"FastCompany -Debunking 3% Research\" href=\"http://www.fastcompany.com/27953/if-your-goal-success-dont-consult-these-gurus\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> and <a title=\"RapidBI debunking 3% Research\" href=\"http://rapidbi.com/harvard-yale-written-goals-study-fact-or-fiction/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>).  At the same time many reading this probably says we don\'t need research to prove the obvious.  The numbers are ridiculous, but the directional truth holds.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">With Prof Matthews\' research, and Vimbli\'s recent transition research, we now have some research to back it up. The key finding from the Vimbli research? People with a personal plan is twice as likely to be top performers than those without.   You can get the full report by <a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"http://eepurl.com/AkdlH\" target=\"_blank\">signing up</a> to this blog. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Research is all good and well, but it is only valuable if we can put it to work.  Vimbli\'s first practical application focus on address this opportunity in the corporate onboarding setting.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The Vimbli solution is still in closed beta, but here is a glimpse of what we are rolling out.  If used correctly Vimbli will deliver (almost) effortless engagement with your sponsor(s), and we believe will result in benefits close to or exceeding the 80% improvement found in the Matthews research.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.  A tool to define your transition.</strong>\r\n\r\na) Basic information\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_372\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-372\" title=\"Mission Setup\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Setup-Mission.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"342\" /> The basic \"Mission\" data for your transition[/caption]\r\n\r\nb) Connectivity goals\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_373\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"798\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-373\" title=\"Mission Connectivity\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Connections-Mission.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"798\" height=\"451\" /> Specific goals related to connectivity[/caption]\r\n\r\nc) Keys to Success\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_374\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"797\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-374\" title=\"Keys to Success\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Keys-to-Success.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"797\" height=\"561\" /> Setting your keys to success requires specific time goals, and keywords to be tracked[/caption]\r\n\r\nd) Ongoing evolution of the transition\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_375\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"787\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-375\" title=\"Mission Notes\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Mission-Notes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"787\" height=\"190\" /> As the mission progress there will be changes. The solution allows you to make ongoing changes.[/caption]\r\n\r\n2. Integration with your Calendar and email to generate automated feedback based on your regular activities.\r\n\r\ni) Secure link with OAUTH 2.0 to Google or Google Apps\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_380\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"577\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-380\" title=\"Link your data\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Link-your-data.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"577\" height=\"467\" /> Vimbli uses OAUTH 2.0 to establish the link with your data (in short this means we don\'t have to ask for your Google login information, the transaction is handled by Google). The data flow is only one-way. Vimbli takes the data into your profile. Vimbli does not upload any data to your Google account.[/caption]\r\n\r\nii) Personal timeline to allow review, editing and adding\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_376\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-376\" title=\"Vimbli Timeline - Illustrative\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Timeline-example.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"570\" /> The timeline contains auto captured and manually added content.[/caption]\r\n\r\n3.  Easy to use personal dashboard\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_379\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"793\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-379\" title=\"Vimbli Personal Dashboard\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Personal-Dashboard.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"793\" height=\"366\" /> Your Mission dashboard displays your progress against the goals you have set. You can make manual adjustments to the progress by moving the dots, or by adding / editing events in your Timeline.[/caption]\r\n\r\n4.  Streamlined communication with your sponsor(s)\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_377\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-377\" title=\"Progress Draft\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the draft progress report generated by Vimbli. The user edits the report before sharing the update with his/ her sponsor(s).[/caption]\r\n\r\n5.  Personal Reflection\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_378\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"482\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-378\" title=\"Personal Reflection\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Reflection.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"482\" height=\"664\" /> On a regular basis (daily?) the user is prompted to complete a reflection. These reflections provide more information to enhance the hard activity data collected by Vimbli.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you have ideas or questions please let us know by leaving a comment.   At the moment we are working through a backlog of beta test requests, but you are welcome to add your name to the <a title=\"Beta waitlist ... \" href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\" target=\"_blank\">list</a>.     If you have a pressing need and want to be bumped to the top of the waitlist use the email option in the footer of this page.','Vimbli can make your transition 80% more successful (and less painful!!)','','publish','open','open','','vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful','','\nhttp://rapidbi.com/harvard-yale-written-goals-study-fact-or-fiction/','2013-06-18 16:43:51','2013-06-18 16:43:51','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/?p=371',0,'post','',0),(372,1,'2013-06-15 15:46:57','2013-06-15 15:46:57','','Mission Setup','The basic \"Mission\" data for your transition','inherit','open','open','','x-setup-mission','','','2013-06-15 15:46:57','2013-06-15 15:46:57','',371,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Setup-Mission.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(373,1,'2013-06-15 15:48:11','2013-06-15 15:48:11','','Mission Connectivity','Specific goals related to connectivity','inherit','open','open','','x-connections-mission','','','2013-06-15 15:48:11','2013-06-15 15:48:11','',371,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Connections-Mission.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),