Easy to use personal dashboard\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_379\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"793\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-379\" title=\"Vimbli Personal Dashboard\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Personal-Dashboard.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"793\" height=\"366\" /> Your Mission dashboard displays your progress against the goals you have set. You can make manual adjustments to the progress by moving the dots, or by adding / editing events in your Timeline.[/caption]\r\n\r\n4.  Streamlined communication with your sponsor(s)\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_377\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-377\" title=\"Progress Draft\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the draft progress report generated by Vimbli. The user edits the report before sharing the update with his/ her sponsor(s).[/caption]\r\n\r\n5.  Personal Reflection\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_378\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"482\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-378\" title=\"Personal Reflection\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Reflection.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"482\" height=\"664\" /> On a regular basis (daily?) the user is prompted to complete a reflection. These reflections provide more information to enhance the hard activity data collected by Vimbli.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you have ideas or questions please let us know by leaving a comment.   At the moment we are working through a backlog of beta test requests, but you are welcome to add your name to the <a title=\"Beta waitlist ... \" href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\" target=\"_blank\">list</a>.     If you have a pressing need and want to be bumped to the top of the waitlist use the email option in the footer of this page.','Vimbli can make your transition 80% more successful (and less painful!!)','','inherit','open','open','','371-revision-2','','','2013-06-15 16:29:34','2013-06-15 16:29:34','',371,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/371-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(384,1,'2013-06-15 16:55:41','2013-06-15 16:55:41','','20130615_094153','Tip #1:  Write your goals down.  It is easy to do, and it works!','inherit','open','open','','20130615_094153','','','2013-06-15 16:55:41','2013-06-15 16:55:41','',359,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/20130615_094153.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(385,1,'2013-06-15 17:06:31','2013-06-15 17:06:31','[caption id=\"attachment_384\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-384\" title=\"20130615_094153\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/20130615_094153-1022x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"641\" /> Tip #1: Write your goals down. It is easy to do, and it works![/caption]\n\nWant to reach more of your goals:  Start by writing your goals down.\n\nRead on to learn more.\n\n<a title=\"About - Michael Hyatt\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/about\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Hyatt</a> recently posted a <a title=\"Michael Hyatt Goal Setting 101\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/goal-setting.html\" target=\"_blank\">Goal Setting</a> guide.  If you are good at setting goals and realizing goals it is worth a read.  If you are so-so at achieving your goals it will definitely be a good return on your time to read the article.\n\nIn the post he describes his 5 principles for goal execution:\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">keep the goals few in number</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">make the goals </span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SMART_criteria\" target=\"_blank\">SMART</a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> (John Richardson </span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" title=\"John\'s SMART worksheet\" href=\"http://personalsuccesstoday.com/goal-setting-worksheet/\" target=\"_blank\">covers</a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> SMART goals)</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">write the goals down</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">review frequently</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">share selectively</span></li>\n</ol>\n<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Michael\'s post aligns well with the onboarding solution we are <a title=\"Make your transition 80 percent more successful\" href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/\" target=\"_blank\">currently testing</a>.  The focus of the solution is to help people make the most of professional transitions.  </span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">  This focus requires the Vimbli solution to prioritize the right things over just getting more done.  In every transition there is a set of things that needs to get done, but transitions are crazy and you need to stay nimble and focused on the transition priorities.  </span>\n\nMichael refers to a report by <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gail-matthews\">Professor Gail Matthews</a> on factors impacting goal completion.  The research is still in progress, but the initial findings are aligned with core message from the recent Vimbli Onboarding report.  The Vimbli report states people with personal plans are twice as likely to be top performers than those without personal plans. (You can get a copy of the report <a title=\"Signup to get the Vimbli report\" href=\"http://eepurl.com/AkdlH\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.)\n\nSpending some time digging into the <a title=\"Prof Matthews\' Goals Research\" href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gailmatthews/researchsummary2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">initial findings</a> of Matthews research is worth it.  <span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">The 3 core findings are listed below.  We used Case 1 as baseline for our impact calculations.  (Case 1:  No written goals, no accountability, no engagement.)</span>\n\n1.  The <strong>80%</strong> Factor.  <em>Engagement</em>:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates they were more likely to achieve success than those who did not reach out regularly.  (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  7.6  Improvement:  78%!)\n\n2.  The <strong>50%</strong> Factor. <em>Accountability</em>: Those who made the commitment to someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not. (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  6.41  Improvement:  50% )\n\n3.  The <strong>40%</strong> Factor. <em>Written commitment</em>:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.\n\nGetting someone to support you on your journey (#2), and keeping up with regular updates (#1) are a challenge.  Writing down your goals is much easier (#3).\n\nAre you already writing down your goals?  Yes? Great!  No? Why not?  If it makes you 40% more likely to achieve the goals ... No excuses. Get started!\n\nOnce you have the goals written down you can look into a service like <a href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/\" target=\"_blank\">Vimbli</a>.  Vimbli makes Engagement and Accountability much easier, but if you don\'t take the first step no solution will help you.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_368\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-368\" title=\"Draft of progress provided by Vimbli\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the automated progress report prepared by Vimbli.<br />(Currently in closed beta.)[/caption]','Write it down ... ','','inherit','open','open','','359-revision-7'