t-size: small;\">Michael\'s post aligns well with the onboarding solution we are <a title=\"Make your transition 80 percent more successful\" href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/\" target=\"_blank\">currently testing</a>.  The focus of the solution is to help people make the most of professional transitions.    This focus requires the Vimbli solution to prioritize the right things over just getting more done.  In every transition there is a set of things that needs to get done, but transitions are crazy and you need to stay nimble and focused on the transition priorities.  </span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Michael refers to a report by <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gail-matthews\">Professor Gail Matthews</a> on factors impacting goal completion.  The research is still in progress, but the initial findings are aligned with core message from the recent Vimbli Onboarding report.  The Vimbli report states people with personal plans are twice as likely to be top performers than those without personal plans. (You can get a copy of the report <a title=\"Signup to get the Vimbli report\" href=\"http://eepurl.com/AkdlH\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.)</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Spending some time digging into the <a title=\"Prof Matthews\' Goals Research\" href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gailmatthews/researchsummary2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">initial findings</a> of Matthews research is worth it.  The 3 core findings are listed below.  We used Case 1 as baseline for our impact calculations.  (Case 1:  No written goals, no accountability, no engagement.)</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">1.  The <strong>80%</strong> Factor.  <em>Engagement</em>:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates they were more likely to achieve success than those who did not reach out regularly.  (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  7.6  Improvement:  78%!)</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">2.  The <strong>50%</strong> Factor. <em>Accountability</em>: Those who made the commitment to someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not. (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  6.41  Improvement:  50% )</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">3.  The <strong>40%</strong> Factor. <em>Written commitment</em>:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Getting someone to support you on your journey (#2), and keeping up with regular updates (#1) are a challenge.  Writing down your goals is much easier (#3).</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Are you already writing down your goals?  Yes? Great!  No? Why not?  If it makes you 40% more likely to achieve the goals ... No excuses. Get started!</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Once you have the goals written you can look into a service like <a href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/\" target=\"_blank\">Vimbli</a>.  Vimbli makes Engagement and Accountability easier, but if you don\'t take the first step no solution will help you. </span>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_368\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-368\" title=\"Draft of progress provided by Vimbli\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the automated progress report prepared by Vimbli.<br />(Currently in closed beta.)[/caption]','Write it down ... ','','inherit','open','open','','359-autosave','','','2013-06-15 17:16:52','2013-06-15 17:16:52','',359,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/359-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(387,1,'2013-06-15 17:06:54','2013-06-15 17:06:54','[caption id=\"attachment_384\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-384\" title=\"20130615_094153\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/20130615_094153-1022x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"641\" /> Tip #1: Write your goals down. It is easy to do, and it works![/caption]\r\n\r\nWant to reach more of your goals:  Start by writing your goals down.\r\n\r\nRead on to learn more.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"About - Michael Hyatt\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/about\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Hyatt</a> recently posted a <a title=\"Michael Hyatt Goal Setting 101\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/goal-setting.html\" target=\"_blank\">Goal Setting</a> guide.  If you are good at setting goals and realizing goals it is worth a read.  If you are so-so at achieving your goals it will definitely be a good return on your time to read the article.\r\n\r\nIn the post he describes his 5 principles for goal execution:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">keep the goals few in number</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">make the goals </span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SMART_criteria\" target=\"_blank\">SMART</a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> (John Richardson </span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" title=\"John\'s SMART worksheet\" href=\"http://personalsuccesstoday.com/goal-setting-worksheet/\" target=\"_blank\">covers</a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> SMART goals)</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">write the goals down</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">review frequently</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">share selectively</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Michael\'s post aligns well with the onboarding solution we are <a title=\"Make your transition 80 percent more successful\" href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/\" target=\"_blank\">currently testing</a>.  The focus of the solution is to help people make the most of professional transitions.  </span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">  This focus requires the Vimbli solution to prioritize the right things over just getting more done.  In every transition there is a set of things that needs to get done, but transitions are crazy and you need to stay nimble and focused on the transition priorities.  </span>\r\n\r\nMichael refers to a report by <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gail-matthews\">Professor Gail Matthews</a> on factors impacting goal completion.  The research is still in progress, but the initial findings are aligned with core message from the recent Vimbli Onboarding report.  The Vimbli report states people with personal plans are twice as likely to be top performers than those without personal plans. (You can get a copy of the report <a title=\"Signup to get the Vimbli report\" href=\"http://eepurl.com/AkdlH\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.)\r\n\r\nSpending some time digging into the <a title=\"Prof Matthews\' Goals Research\" href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gailmatthews/researchsummary2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">initial findings</a> of Matthews research is worth it.  <span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">The 3 core findings are listed below.  We used Case 1 as baseline for our impact calculations.  (Case 1:  No written goals, no accountability, no engagement.)</span>\r\n\r\n1.  The <strong>80%</strong> Factor.  <em>Engagement</em>:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates they were more likely to achieve success than those who did not reach out regularly.  (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  7.6  Improvement:  78%!)\r\n\r\n2.  The <strong>50%</strong> Factor. <em>Accountability</em>: Those who made the commitment to someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not. (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  6.41  Improvement:  50% )\r\n\r\n3.  The <strong>40%</strong> Factor. <em>Written commitment</em>:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.\r\n\r\nGetting someone to support you on your journey (#2), and keeping up with regular updates (#1) are a challenge.  Writing down your goals is much easier (#3).\r\n\r\nAre you already writing down your goals?  Yes? Great!  No? Why not?  If it makes you 40% more likely to achieve the goals ... No excuses. Get started!\r\n\r\nOnce you have the goals written you can look into a service like <a href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/\" target=\"_blank\">Vimbli</a>.  Vimbli makes Engagement and Accountability easier, but if you don\'t take the first step no solution will help you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_368\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-368\" title=\"Draft of progress provided by Vimbli\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the automated progress report prepared by Vimbli.<br />(Currently in closed beta.)[/caption]','Write it down ... ','','inherit','open','open','','359-revision-8','','','2013-06-15 17:06:54','2013-06-15 17:06:54','',359,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/359-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(388,1,'2013-06-15 17:08:43','2013-06-15 17:08:43','[caption id=\"attachment_384\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-384\" title=\"20130615_094153\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/20130615_094153-1022x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"641\" /> Tip #1: Write your goals down. It is easy to do, and it works![/caption]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Want to reach more of your goals:  Start by writing your goals down.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Read on to learn more.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><a title=\"About - Michael Hyatt\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/about\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Hyatt</a> recently posted a <a title=\"Michael Hyatt Goal Setting 101\" href=\"http://michaelhyatt.com/goal-setting.html\" target=\"_blank\">Goal Setting</a> guide.  If you are good at setting goals and realizing goals it is worth a read.  If you are so-so at achieving your goals it will definitely be a good return on your time to read the article.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">In the post he describes his 5 principles for goal execution:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">keep the goals few in number</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">make the goals <a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SMART_criteria\" target=\"_blank\">SMART</a> (John Richardson <a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" title=\"John\'s SMART worksheet\" href=\"http://personalsuccesstoday.com/goal-setting-worksheet/\" target=\"_blank\">covers</a> SMART goals)</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">write the goals down</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">review frequently</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">share selectively</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Michael\'s post aligns well with the onboarding solution we are <a title=\"Make your transition 80 percent more successful\" href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/\" target=\"_blank\">currently testing</a>.  The focus of the solution is to help people make the most of professional transitions.    This focus requires the Vimbli solution to prioritize the right things over just getting more done.  In every transition there is a set of things that needs to get done, but transitions are crazy and you need to stay nimble and focused on the transition priorities.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Michael refers to a report by <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gail-matthews\">Professor Gail Matthews</a> on factors impacting goal completion.  The research is still in progress, but the initial findings are aligned with core message from the recent Vimbli Onboarding report.  The Vimbli report states people with personal plans are twice as likely to be top performers than those without personal plans. (You can get a copy of the report <a title=\"Signup to get the Vimbli report\" href=\"http://eepurl.com/AkdlH\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Spending some time digging into the <a title=\"Prof Matthews\' Goals Research\" href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gailmatthews/researchsummary2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">initial findings</a> of Matthews research is worth it.  The 3 core findings are listed below.  We used Case 1 as baseline for our impact calculations.  (Case 1:  No written goals, no accountability, no engagement.)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">1.  The <strong>80%</strong> Factor.  <em>Engagement</em>:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates they were more likely to achieve success than those who did not reach out regularly.  (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  7.6  Improvement:  78%!)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">2.  The <strong>50%</strong> Factor. <em>Accountability</em>: Those who made the commitment to someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not. (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  6.41  Improvement:  50% )</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">3.  The <strong>40%</strong> Factor. <em>Written commitment</em>:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Getting someone to support you on your journey (#2), and keeping up with regular updates (#1) are a challenge.  Writing down your goals is much easier (#3).</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Are you already writing down your goals?  Yes? Great!  No? Why not?  If it makes you 40% more likely to achieve the goals ... No excuses. Get started!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Once you have the goals written you can look into a service like <a href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/vimbli-can-make-your-transition-80-more-successful-and-less-painful/\" target=\"_blank\">Vimbli</a>.  Vimbli makes Engagement and Accountability easier, but if you don\'t take the first step no solution will help you. </span>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_368\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-368\" title=\"Draft of progress provided by Vimbli\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the automated progress report prepared by Vimbli.<br />(Currently in closed beta.)[/caption]','Write it down ... ','','inherit','open','open','','359-revision-9','','','2013-06-15 17:08:43','2013-06-15 17:08:43','',359,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/359-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(389,1,'2013-06-15 16:31:29','2013-06-15 16:31:29','I<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">nitial <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gailmatthews/researchsummary2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">findings</a> by <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gail-matthews\" target=\"_blank\">Prof Gail Matthews</a> show that you are more likely to meet your goals if you do certain things.  A lot more likely.   Here are the 3 things you need to build into your execution plan:</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">1.  The <strong>80%</strong> Factor.  <em>Engagement</em>:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates they were more likely to be successful than those who did not reach out regularly.  (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  7.6  Improvement:  78%!)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">2.  The <strong>50%</strong> Factor. <em>Accountability</em>: Those who shared their goals with someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not. (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  6.41  Improvement:  50% )</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">3.  The <strong>40%</strong> Factor. <em>Written commitment</em>:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The findings align well with the mythical 3% success research by Harvard Business School (HBS) or Yale.   You can pick the most prestigious one when you quote the \"research\" at the next cocktail party or tailgate ;) .  The myth goes like this: 3% of the graduating class (1953 or 1979?) had written goals. Twenty (or 10) years later the 3% earned 10 times what the \"no clear goals\"-group did ... well, it is just a myth (<a title=\"FastCompany -Debunking 3% Research\" href=\"http://www.fastcompany.com/27953/if-your-goal-success-dont-consult-these-gurus\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> and <a title=\"RapidBI debunking 3% Research\" href=\"http://rapidbi.com/harvard-yale-written-goals-study-fact-or-fiction/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>).  At the same time many reading this probably says we don\'t need research to prove the obvious.  The numbers are ridiculous, but the directional truth holds.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">With Prof Matthews\' research, and Vimbli\'s recent transition research, we now have some research to back it up. The key finding from the Vimbli research? People with a personal plan is twice as likely to be top performers than those without.   You can get the full report by <a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"http://eepurl.com/AkdlH\" target=\"_blank\">signing up</a> to this blog. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Research is all good and well, but it is only valuable if we can put it to work.  Vimbli\'s first practical application focus on address this opportunity in the corporate onboarding setting.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The Vimbli solution is still in closed beta, but here is a glimpse of what we are rolling out.  If used correctly Vimbli will deliver (almost) effortless engagement with your sponsor(s), and we believe will result in benefits close to or exceeding the 80% improvement found in the Matthews research.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.  A tool to define your transition.</strong>\r\n\r\na) Basic information\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_372\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-372\" title=\"Mission Setup\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Setup-Mission.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"342\" /> The basic \"Mission\" data for your transition[/caption]\r\n\r\nb) Connectivity goals\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_373\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"798\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-373\" title=\"Mission Connectivity\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Connections-Mission.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"798\" height=\"451\" /> Specific goals related to connectivity[/caption]\r\n\r\nc) Keys to Success\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_374\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"797\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-374\" title=\"Keys to Success\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Keys-to-Success.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"797\" height=\"561\" /> Setting your keys to success requires specific time goals, and keywords to be tracked[/caption]\r\n\r\nd) Ongoing evolution of the transition\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_375\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"787\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-375\" title=\"Mission Notes\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Mission-Notes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"787\" height=\"190\" /> As the mission progress there will be changes. The solution allows you to make ongoing changes.[/caption]\r\n\r\n2. Integration with your Calendar and email to generate automated feedback based on your regular activities.\r\n\r\ni) Secure link with OAUTH 2.0 to Google or Google Apps\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_380\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"577\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-380\" title=\"Link your data\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Link-your-data.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"577\" height=\"467\" /> Vimbli uses OAUTH 2.0 to establish the link with your data (in short this means we don\'t have to ask for your Google login information, the transaction is handled by Google). The data flow is only one-way. Vimbli takes the data into your profile. Vimbli does not upload any data to your Google account.[/caption]\r\n\r\nii) Personal timeline to allow review, editing and adding\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_376\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-376\" title=\"Vimbli Timeline - Illustrative\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Timeline-example.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"570\" /> The timeline contains auto captured and manually added content.[/caption]\r\n\r\n3.  Easy to use personal dashboard\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_379\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"793\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-379\" title=\"Vimbli Personal Dashboard\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Personal-Dashboard.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"793\" height=\"366\" /> Your Mission dashboard displays your progress against the goals you have set. You can make manual adjustments to the progress by moving the dots, or by adding / editing events in your Timeline.[/caption]\r\n\r\n4.  Streamlined communication with your sponsor(s)\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_377\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-377\" title=\"Progress Draft\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the draft progress report generated by Vimbli. The user edits the report before sharing the update with his/ her sponsor(s).[/caption]\r\n\r\n5.  Personal Reflection\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_378\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"482\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-378\" title=\"Personal Reflection\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Reflection.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"482\" height=\"664\" /> On a regular basis (daily?) the user is prompted to complete a reflection. These reflections provide more information to enhance the hard activity data collected by Vimbli.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you have ideas or questions please let us know by leaving a comment.   At the moment we are working through a backlog of beta test requests, but you are welcome to add your name to the <a title=\"Beta waitlist ... \" href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\" target=\"_blank\">list</a>.     If you have a pressing need and want to be bumped to the top of the waitlist use the email option in the footer of this page.','Vimbli can make your transition 80% more successful (and less painful!!)','','inherit','open','open','','371-revision-3','','','2013-06-15 16:31:29','2013-06-15 16:31:29','',371,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/371-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(390,1,'2013-06-15 17:09:52','2013-06-15 17:09:52','Initial <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gailmatthews/researchsummary2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">findings</a> by <a href=\"http://www.dominican.edu/academics/ahss/undergraduate-programs-1/psych/faculty/fulltime/gail-matthews\" target=\"_blank\">Prof Gail Matthews</a> show that you are more likely to meet your goals if you do certain things.  A lot more likely.\r\n\r\nHere are the 3 things the research suggests you should consider for your next your plan or set of goals:\r\n\r\n1.  The <strong>80%</strong> Factor.  <em>Engagement</em>:  If participants engaged their accountability contact with weekly updates they were more likely to be successful than those who did not reach out regularly.  (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  7.6  Improvement:  78%!)\r\n\r\n2.  The <strong>50%</strong> Factor. <em>Accountability</em>: Those who shared their goals with someone specific were more likely to be successful than those who did not. (Baseline:  4.28,  Engaged:  6.41  Improvement:  50% )\r\n\r\n3.  The <strong>40%</strong> Factor. <em>Written commitment</em>:  Those who wrote down their commitment were more likely to be successful that those who did not.  Independent of them having an accountable person, or a regular engagement cadence.\r\n\r\nThe findings align well with the mythical 3% success research by Harvard Business School (HBS) or Yale.   You can pick the most prestigious one when you quote the \"research\" at the next cocktail party or tailgate ;) .  The myth goes like this: <span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">3% of the graduating class (1953 or 1979?) had written goals. Twenty (or 10) years </span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">later the 3% earned 10 times what the \"</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">no clear goals\"-group did ... well, it is just a myth (<a title=\"FastCompany -Debunking 3% Research\" href=\"http://www.fastcompany.com/27953/if-your-goal-success-dont-consult-these-gurus\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> and <a title=\"RapidBI debunking 3% Research\" href=\"http://rapidbi.com/harvard-yale-written-goals-study-fact-or-fiction/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>).  At the same time many reading this probably says we don\'t need research to prove the obvious.  The numbers are ridiculous, but the directional truth holds.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">With Prof Matthews\' research, and Vimbli\'s recent transition research, we now have some research to back it up. The key finding from the </span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Vimbli research? People with a personal plan is twice as likely to be top performers than those without.   You can get the full report by </span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"http://eepurl.com/AkdlH\" target=\"_blank\">signing up</a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> to this blog. </span>\r\n\r\nResearch is all good and well, but it is only valuable if we can put it to work.  Vimbli\'s first practical application focus on address this opportunity in the corporate onboarding setting.\r\n\r\nThe Vimbli solution is still in closed beta, but here is a glimpse of what we are rolling out.  If used correctly Vimbli will deliver (almost) effortless engagement with your sponsor(s), and we believe will result in benefits close to or exceeding the 80% improvement found in the Matthews research.\r\n\r\n<strong>1.  A tool to define your transition.</strong>\r\n\r\na) Basic information\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_372\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-372\" title=\"Mission Setup\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Setup-Mission.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"342\" /> The basic \"Mission\" data for your transition[/caption]\r\n\r\nb) Connectivity goals\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_373\" align=\"align