\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"577\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-380\" title=\"Link your data\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Link-your-data.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"577\" height=\"467\" /> Vimbli uses OAUTH 2.0 to establish the link with your data (in short this means we don\'t have to ask for your Google login information, the transaction is handled by Google). The data flow is only one-way. Vimbli takes the data into your profile. Vimbli does not upload any data to your Google account.[/caption]\r\n\r\nii) Personal timeline to allow review, editing and adding\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_376\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-376\" title=\"Vimbli Timeline - Illustrative\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Timeline-example.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"570\" /> The timeline contains auto captured and manually added content.[/caption]\r\n\r\n3.  Easy to use personal dashboard\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_379\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"793\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-379\" title=\"Vimbli Personal Dashboard\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Personal-Dashboard.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"793\" height=\"366\" /> Your Mission dashboard displays your progress against the goals you have set. You can make manual adjustments to the progress by moving the dots, or by adding / editing events in your Timeline.[/caption]\r\n\r\n4.  Streamlined communication with your sponsor(s)\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_377\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"913\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-377\" title=\"Progress Draft\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Progress-Draft1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"913\" height=\"466\" /> An example of the draft progress report generated by Vimbli. The user edits the report before sharing the update with his/ her sponsor(s).[/caption]\r\n\r\n5.  Personal Reflection\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_378\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"482\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-378\" title=\"Personal Reflection\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/X-Reflection.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"482\" height=\"664\" /> On a regular basis (daily?) the user is prompted to complete a reflection. These reflections provide more information to enhance the hard activity data collected by Vimbli.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you have ideas or questions please let us know by leaving a comment.   At the moment we are working through a backlog of beta test requests, but you are welcome to add your name to the <a title=\"Beta waitlist ... \" href=\"http://signmeup.vimbli.com/\" target=\"_blank\">list</a>.     If you have a pressing need and want to be bumped to the top of the waitlist use the email option in the footer of this page.','Vimbli can make your transition 80% more successful (and less painful!!)','','inherit','open','open','','371-revision-5','','','2013-06-15 18:38:49','2013-06-15 18:38:49','',371,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/371-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(393,1,'2013-06-19 12:28:22','2013-06-19 12:28:22','','Cathedralandtentviaistock','What is your vision? Cathedral and/ or Tent ... Both could be great depending on your vision and situation. ','inherit','open','open','','cathedralandtentviaistock-2','','','2013-06-19 12:28:22','2013-06-19 12:28:22','',80,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Cathedralandtentviaistock.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(394,1,'2013-03-29 18:06:23','2013-03-29 18:06:23','Progress and personal growth does not happen without change.  Every moment of significant progress and personal growth is preceded by a transition of some sort.\r\n\r\nOften these transitions are traumatic, and can be somewhat painful.  A new job, a new city, a new company, a new relationship …\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_184\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-184   \" title=\"Your Vision\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/beta/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Cathedralandtentviaistock-300x118.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"118\" /> What is your vision? Cathedral and/ or Tent ...[/caption]\r\n\r\nNo one transition looks the same, but successful transitions have common elements.  A successful transition requires a lot of effort and focus, but there are 5 common elements:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Your VISION</strong> of what success looks like:  Are you building cathedral, building a shack or pitching a tent.  Your answer will impact everything you do.  If you don’t have an answer you’ll probably need to buckle up for a bumpy ride ‘til you find the vision, and find the sponsor who shares the vision with you.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Your PLAN</strong>, with building blocks:  Something worthwhile needs you to do a few things, and to do the things well.  What the things are often differ, but in most cases a transition requires building and maintaining relationships.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Your Execution: </strong> Plans are great, but in the case of your own life you have to go and execute your plan.  Many other things in life you can get others to do for you.  Your life you have to live yourself.  Having others with you makes the journey more fun, but you need to do the living.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Your R<span style=\"color: #000000;\">eflection</span>: </strong> Few plans actually work out as planned.  Hence the name, \"Plan\".  Reflecting on your progress (and where possible working with your sponsor and possibly some advisors and supporters) is critical.  Regular reflection allow you to identify what work and what does not.  In many ways that is what a journal done well achieves.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Your Adjustments: </strong>Many people reflect, and reflect but never take action on the reflection.  Reflection impacts your plan in 2 ways.  You can decide something is working, and do more of it OR you can decide something is not working and make a change.  The latter catergory also includes achieved goals.  Celebrate your achievements. Celebrate your failures. Learn from it, make adjustments and move forward.  Sometimes the learning process takes a bit longer, and it is ok to give yourself time to complete the process.<strong>   </strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"line-height: 24px;\">\r\n</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Without the explicit commitment to do the reviews and adjustments you should not waste time on #1, #2 and #3.  Go and buy a lottery ticket instead.  Ok, maybe this is a bit harsh.  The truth is without Reflection on and Adjustments to your plan your life journey will be less complete.   Note that true reflection may lead you to opt to do less not more.  Each of us is unique.  You need to learn more about yourself, and live your life.  Just like I need to learn more about myself and live my life.  </span>\r\n\r\nYou read this and it sounds black and white you need to figure out where you want to add your own color.  The elements identified give only the starting point for you to create your own transition. You have to make adjustments to fit your worldview, personality and capabilities, and also align with the company culture and the immediate business needs.\r\n\r\nIn future posts we’ll cover the elements in detail and also discuss how to personalize the approach to fit you and your situation.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime – What is your secret to a successful transition? If you have different tips for different transitions feel free to share.','How to make change count!','','inherit','open','open','','80-revision-16','','','2013-03-29 18:06:23','2013-03-29 18:06:23','',80,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/80-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(395,1,'2013-06-19 12:30:25','2013-06-19 12:30:25','<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Progress and personal growth does not happen withou