yle=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Your R<span style=\"color: #000000;\">eflection</span>: </strong> Few plans actually work out as planned.  Hence the name, \"Plan\".  Reflecting on your progress (and where possible working with your sponsor and possibly some advisors and supporters) is critical.  Regular reflection allow you to identify what work and what does not.  In many ways that is what a journal done well achieves.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Your Adjustments: </strong>Many people reflect, and reflect but never take action on the reflection.  Reflection impacts your plan in 2 ways.  You can decide something is working, and do more of it OR you can decide something is not working and make a change.  The latter catergory also includes achieved goals.  Celebrate your achievements. Celebrate your failures. Learn from it, make adjustments and move forward.  Sometimes the learning process takes a bit longer, and it is ok to give yourself time to complete the process.<strong>   </strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Without the explicit commitment to do the reviews and adjustments you should not waste time on #1, #2 and #3.  Go and buy a lottery ticket instead.  Ok, maybe this is a bit harsh.  The truth is without Reflection on and Adjustments to your plan your life journey will be less complete.   Note that true reflection may lead you to opt to do less not more.  Each of us is unique.  You need to learn more about yourself, and live your life.  Just like I need to learn more about myself and live my life.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You read this and it sounds black and white you need to figure out where you want to add your own color.  The elements identified give only the starting point for you to create your own transition. You have to make adjustments to fit your worldview, personality and capabilities, and also align with the company culture and the immediate business needs.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In future posts we’ll cover the elements in detail and also discuss how to personalize the approach to fit you and your situation.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In the meantime – What is your secret to a successful transition? If you have different tips for different transitions feel free to share.</span>','How to make change count!','','inherit','open','open','','80-revision-17','','','2013-06-19 12:30:25','2013-06-19 12:30:25','',80,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/80-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(396,1,'2013-06-19 13:33:40','2013-06-19 13:33:40','','logo-180','','inherit','open','open','','logo-180','','','2013-06-19 13:33:40','2013-06-19 13:33:40','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/logo-180.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(397,1,'2013-06-19 13:33:42','2013-06-19 13:33:42','','logo-1024','','inherit','open','open','','logo-1024-2','','','2013-06-19 13:33:42','2013-06-19 13:33:42','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/logo-1024.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(398,1,'2013-06-19 13:33:45','2013-06-19 13:33:45','','vimbli square icon','','inherit','open','open','','vimbli-square-icon-2','','','2013-06-19 13:33:45','2013-06-19 13:33:45','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/vimbli-square-icon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(400,1,'2013-06-24 03:48:04','2013-06-24 03:48:04','[caption id=\"attachment_404\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"604\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-404\" title=\"Hennie Junior and Senior, 1973? Isilimela.  Transkei. South Africa. \" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/6733_109417881614_5502440_n-002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"604\" height=\"402\" /> 1973? Isilimela. Transkei. South Africa.[/caption]\r\n\r\nThanks to all responses!  My wife liked this comment a lot: <strong>Don\'t volunteer yourself to do what she \'asks\' you to do. Do it before she asks. </strong>\r\n\r\nThe detail responses make for <a title=\"Dad survey - June 2013\" href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Dad-plan-Survey-Results-June-23.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">a good read</a> as dad-to-be, and I expect parents in general will enjoy reading it.  The range of responses is wide. You\'ll find things you like, and things you laugh at! and you\'ll probably have a good discussion with your partner on why you decided on your approach (and why you are/ were right!).\r\n\r\nThe summary of the \"research\" effort is:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The change is personal.  You need to figure it out yourself.</li>\r\n	<li>Most agree on the following to do\'s  Create time for the mom, and be a true partner.   How you do it is up to you.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIn the written responses there are several gems. Here are a few:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Accepting the fact that this is truly FOR LIFE!    Nothing that you have done will have as big an impact on your life.  Your kids remains your kids for the rest of your life...</li>\r\n	<li>It was all a blur. Got home with baby and thought: \"Now what!? Help!\".</li>\r\n	<li>No \"markers.\" it\'s a journey, not a destination.</li>\r\n	<li>One job at a time.  Keep yourself from thinking about the child in the aggregate - you\'ll go crazy.</li>\r\n	<li>...enjoy the ride, and always remember that the child isn\'t really yours...but rather us simply \"on loan\" from the Father above!</li>\r\n	<li>Kids spell love like this: TIME</li>\r\n	<li>Be sure to find time to focus on you as a couple. The kid(s) will move out but you will be together so you need to continuously invest in your relationship as a couple.</li>\r\n	<li>Enjoy the moment. It is fleeting. And don\'t panic! Babies are far more resilient than we give them credit for.</li>\r\n	<li>Being a father is the best job I have ever had.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDownload the cleaned-up responses <a title=\"Dad survey - June 2013\" href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Dad-plan-Survey-Results-June-23.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Wisdom from Dads ... for dads ','','publish','open','open','','wisdom-from-dads-for-dads','','','2013-06-24 03:50:11','2013-06-24 03:50:11','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/?p=400',0,'post','',0),(401,1,'2013-06-19 13:36:27','2013-06-19 13:36:27','','logo-1024','','inherit','open','open','','logo-1024-3','','','2013-06-19 13:36:27','2013-06-19 13:36:27','',400,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/logo-10241.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(402,1,'2013-06-19 13:37:10','2013-06-19 13:37:10','<a href=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/logo-10241.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-401\" title=\"logo-1024\" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/logo-10241-300x146.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"146\" /></a>','','','inherit','open','open','','400-revision','','','2013-06-19 13:37:10','2013-06-19 13:37:10','',400,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/400-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(404,1,'2013-06-24 03:38:34','2013-06-24 03:38:34','','Hennie Junior and Senior, 1973? Isilimela.  Transkei. South Africa. ','1973? Isilimela.  Transkei. South Africa. ','inherit','open','open','','6733_109417881614_5502440_n-002','','','2013-06-24 03:38:34','2013-06-24 03:38:34','',400,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/6733_109417881614_5502440_n-002.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(405,1,'2013-06-24 03:42:03','2013-06-24 03:42:03','[caption id=\"attachment_404\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"604\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-404\" title=\"Hennie Junior and Senior, 1973? Isilimela.  Transkei. South Africa. \" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/6733_109417881614_5502440_n-002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"604\" height=\"402\" /> 1973? Isilimela. Transkei. South Africa.[/caption]\n\nThanks to all responses!  My wife liked this comment a lot: <strong>Don\'t volunteer yourself to do what she \'asks\' you to do. Do it before she asks.  </strong>\n\nThe detail responses make for a good read as dad-to-be, and I expect parents in general will enjoy reading it.  The range of responses is wide. You\'ll find things you like, and things you laugh at! and you\'ll probably have a good discussion with your partner on why you decided on your approach (and why you are/ were right! ;) ) .\n\nThe summary of the \"research\" effort is:\n<ol>\n	<li>The change is personal.  You need to figure it out yourself.</li>\n	<li>Most agree on the following to do\'s  Create time for the mom, and be a true partner.   How you do it is up to you.</li>\n</ol>\nIn the written responses there were several gems. Here are a few examples:\n<ul>\n	<li>Accepting the fact that this is truly FOR LIFE!    Nothing that you have done will have as big an impact on your life.  Your kids remains your kids for the rest of your life...</li>\n	<li>It was all a blur. Got home with baby and thought: \"Now what!? Help!\".</li>\n	<li>No \"markers.\" it\'s a journey, not a destination.</li>\n	<li>One job at a time.  Keep yourself from thinking about the child in the aggregate - you\'ll go crazy.</li>\n	<li>...enjoy the ride, and always remember that the child isn\'t really yours...but rather us simply \"on loan\" from the Father above!</li>\n	<li>Kids spell love like this: TIME</li>\n	<li>Be sure to find time to focus on you as a couple. The kid(s) will move out but you will be together so you need to continuously invest in your relationship as a couple.</li>\n	<li>Enjoy the moment. It is fleeting. And don\'t panic! Babies are far more resilient than we give them credit for.</li>\n	<li>Being a father is the best job I have ever had.</li>\n</ul>\nDownload the cleaned-up responses here.\n\n&nbsp;','Wisdom from Dads ... ','','inherit','open','open','','400-revision-2','','','2013-06-24 03:42:03','2013-06-24 03:42:03','',400,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/400-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(435,1,'2013-08-22 18:15:40','2013-08-22 18:15:40','','Dad-plan Survey Results - June 23','From Dads to Dads ... what matters in the first few weeks!','inherit','open','open','','dad-plan-survey-results-june-23','','','2013-08-22 18:15:40','2013-08-22 18:15:40','',0,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Dad-plan-Survey-Results-June-23.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(407,1,'2013-06-24 03:42:10','2013-06-24 03:42:10','[caption id=\"attachment_404\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"604\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-404\" title=\"Hennie Junior and Senior, 1973? Isilimela.  Transkei. South Africa. \" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/6733_109417881614_5502440_n-002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"604\" height=\"402\" /> 1973? Isilimela. Transkei. South Africa.[/caption]\r\n\r\nThanks to all responses!  My wife liked this comment a lot: <strong>Don\'t volunteer yourself to do what she \'asks\' you to do. Do it before she asks.  </strong>\r\n\r\nThe detail responses make for a good read as dad-to-be, and I expect parents in general will enjoy reading it.  The range of responses is wide. You\'ll find things you like, and things you laugh at! and you\'ll probably have a good discussion with your partner on why you decided on your approach (and why you are/ were right! ;) ) .\r\n\r\nThe summary of the \"research\" effort is:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The change is personal.  You need to figure it out yourself.</li>\r\n	<li>Most agree on the following to do\'s  Create time for the mom, and be a true partner.   How you do it is up to you.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIn the written responses there were several gems. Here are a few examples:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Accepting the fact that this is truly FOR LIFE!    Nothing that you have done will have as big an impact on your life.  Your kids remains your kids for the rest of your life...</li>\r\n	<li>It was all a blur. Got home with baby and thought: \"Now what!? Help!\".</li>\r\n	<li>No \"markers.\" it\'s a journey, not a destination.</li>\r\n	<li>One job at a time.  Keep yourself from thinking about the child in the aggregate - you\'ll go crazy.</li>\r\n	<li>...enjoy the ride, and always remember that the child isn\'t really yours...but rather us simply \"on loan\" from the Father above!</li>\r\n	<li>Kids spell love like this: TIME</li>\r\n	<li>Be sure to find time to focus on you as a couple. The kid(s) will move out but you will be together so you need to continuously invest in your relationship as a couple.</li>\r\n	<li>Enjoy the moment. It is fleeting. And don\'t panic! Babies are far more resilient than we give them credit for.</li>\r\n	<li>Being a father is the best job I have ever had.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDownload the cleaned-up responses here.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Wisdom from Dads ... ','','inherit','open','open','','400-revision-3','','','2013-06-24 03:42:10','2013-06-24 03:42:10','',400,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/400-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(408,1,'2013-06-24 03:43:33','2013-06-24 03:43:33','[caption id=\"attachment_404\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"604\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-404\" title=\"Hennie Junior and Senior, 1973? Isilimela.  Transkei. South Africa. \" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/6733_109417881614_5502440_n-002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"604\" height=\"402\" /> 1973? Isilimela. Transkei. South Africa.[/caption]\r\n\r\nThanks to all responses!  My wife liked this comment a lot: <strong>Don\'t volunteer yourself to do what she \'asks\' you to do. Do it before she asks.  </strong>\r\n\r\nThe detail responses make for a good read as dad-to-be, and I expect parents in general will enjoy reading it.  The range of responses is wide. You\'ll find things you like, and things you laugh at! and you\'ll probably have a good discussion with your partner on why you decided on your approach (and why you are/ were right! ;) ) .\r\n\r\nThe summary of the \"research\" effort is:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The change is personal.  You need to figure it out yourself.</li>\r\n	<li>Most agree on the following to do\'s  Create time for the mom, and be a true partner.   How you do it is up to you.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIn the written responses there were several gems. Here are a few examples:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Accepting the fact that this is truly FOR LIFE!    Nothing that you have done will have as big an impact on your life.  Your kids remains your kids for the rest of your life...</li>\r\n	<li>It was all a blur. Got home with baby and thought: \"Now what!? Help!\".</li>\r\n	<li>No \"markers.\" it\'s a journey, not a destination.</li>\r\n	<li>One job at a time.  Keep yourself from thinking about the child in the aggregate - you\'ll go crazy.</li>\r\n	<li>...enjoy the ride, and always remember that the child isn\'t really yours...but rather us simply \"on loan\" from the Father above!</li>\r\n	<li>Kids spell love like this: TIME</li>\r\n	<li>Be sure to find time to focus on you as a couple. The kid(s) will move out but you will be together so you need to continuously invest in your relationship as a couple.</li>\r\n	<li>Enjoy the moment. It is fleeting. And don\'t panic! Babies are far more resilient than we give them credit for.</li>\r\n	<li>Being a father is the best job I have ever had.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDownload the cleaned-up responses here.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Wisdom from Dads ... for dads ','','inherit','open','open','','400-revision-4','','','2013-06-24 03:43:33','2013-06-24 03:43:33','',400,'http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/400-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(409,1,'2013-06-24 03:47:54','2013-06-24 03:47:54','[caption id=\"attachment_404\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"604\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-404\" title=\"Hennie Junior and Senior, 1973? Isilimela.  Transkei. South Africa. \" src=\"http://vimbli.com/app/webroot/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/6733_109417881614_5502440_n-002.jpg\" alt=\"\